name: Mushroom Dome Retreat & the LAND of Paradise Suite
description:
June 11th and 12th just opened up! Want a last minute reservation?
We have been listing the Mushroom Dome Retreat and the LAND of Paradise Suite with airbnb since July '09 and have had the most reservations of any of their listings. There is a reason we are so popular: the cabin is near a Redwood Grove, and at night, there is hardly any sound here - maybe crickets. It is a Paradise here: a great place to unwind & restore. Even when it rains!
neighborhood_overview:
Even though we live only an 8-10 minute drive to Aptos village and the beaches, as we live on 10 acres, it feels very remote and private here. It is usually very quiet at night - sometimes we can hear the ocean waves crashing on the beach. There is lots of land to hike on and explore here as well.
We have 9 people living here in a rather loose community.
host_about:
We live on 10 beautiful acres of sun, oak forest, redwood groves and gardens with a parrot, 2 cats, a small dog, 12 chickens and from 200 - 500 hummingbirds - depending on the time of year..  

I have been hosting on airbnb since July, 2009 and really love what this company has made possible. I have met so many wonderful people from around the world that I would never have met if I hadn't had this opportunity with airbnb! Some of our guests (especially the ones from Europe) have never seen a hummingbird before and here they get to see them up close - just a few feet from them as the birds "hum" around the feeders.

We welcome you to come experience the peace and tranquility that our wonderful land has to offer.

name: Surf cottage Pleasure Point walk to surf/ coffee
description:
Private free standing beach cottage w/hot tub. Walk to surf/beach/coffee/food
Comfy & cozy in the prime location to surf, have a surf lesson, have a beach day or just watch surfers catch waves all day. Conveniently located close to coffee, restaurants, markets, the beach and more. Remote work here. Healing, tranquil & relaxing. The PRIVATE hot tub just completes that experience. :-) Upon approval we can accept 1 small/medium size dog, just please no cats. $100 additional pet cleaning fee
neighborhood_overview: I love everything about this neighborhood.  I love how I know my neighbors.  I love how walking down to check the surf is difficult just because of the friends you see along the way.  We don't have sidewalks and we like it that way. What we have are backyard bbqs and each other.
host_about: Hey Airbnb folks thanks for taking the time to check out my profile.  I've spent most of my life in Santa Cruz and I am a big fan of keeping the integrity of Pleasure Point, architecturally and as a community. Traveling and surfing are a few of the greatest loves in my life. There is so much to be learned from people and places. My love for surfing has taken me across the globe.  Enjoy this sweet little shpot in the heart of Pleasure Point.

name: Guest bedroom in Victorian home
description: More than 500 guests have written positive reviews, detailing how much they've appreciated a peaceful, quiet stay in my house.
neighborhood_overview: The West side of Santa Cruz is an extension, uphill, from the historic Mission Plaza.  It is one of the original 'neighbourhoods' in Santa Cruz with many mid-late 1800s homes providing spectacular panoramic views of Monterey Bay.  My house was an original 'settler' homestead, built in the 1860s in one of the finest locations then and now.
host_about:
I am a phonetician, speech technologist, and linguist. 
Apart from my professional work, I enjoy my unique Victorian house, gardening, growing orchids, cooking and fine wines, antiques, painting, hiking, camping under the stars, international travel, and, most of all, my gorgeous Bengal cat.
This is a quiet, non-smoking, cat-loving house where dogs would have a hard time but cat-lovers will be delighted!

name: Guest Cottage with shared bath
description:
30 day minimum
Tiny garden cottage with a small kitchenette and small sleeping loft with a full futon. This is a very cute, very cozy space -- perfect for a single person or a couple. The loft has a low ceiling -- think ship's bunk. .
Bathroom in main house (the cottage does not have its own bathroom).
There's a 30 night min/max to stay in compliance with County rules but longer stays are also an option.
We have cats and dogs. Visiting pets are welcome but there's a fee.
host_about:
I am an over employed PA in love with the country life. The property is a rambling half acre of flowers, vegetable gardens an fruit trees in the hilly setting of South Santa Cruz County. Large sunny decks flank the main house and invite guests outside to enjoy morning coffee and the New York Times. 
The house has a small downstairs bedroom with shared bath. There is also a much larger private suite of rooms upstairs (that is not listed).  The guest cottage is quite small but cozy and is sited under the trees at the bottom of the rose garden. It has a small kitchenette and shares the downstairs bathroom in the main house. Both the bedroom and the cottage have queen sized futons. The cottage sleeping loft is a short ladder climb up. Either space would be perfect for a couple. We can accommodate up to three couples, with children. Well behaved dogs are also welcome and guests are encouraged to cook in the main house in the country-style kitchen with oak floors and an antique gas stove . 
The outdoor spaces offer benches and tables to sit, read and even eat out doors. And the wood fired hot tub is quite popular. I especially love soaking under the stars....
I serve coffee in the morning if I am home and not working out of town.

name: Ridge Top Get-A-Way and Quiet Dedicated work space
description:
A quite, private suite in a beautiful Ridge Top setting. An experience to refresh and revive you!
The guest suite (2 bedrooms, Private spa bathroom & private deck) occupies the lower floor of our hilltop home. Enjoy forest views and quite starry nights, 20 mins to either Silicon Valley or Monterey Bay beaches. Guest have a private entrance and off street parking is provided.
neighborhood_overview: What we love about our neighborhood is that we don't live in a neighborhood. Our house sits on a sunny hilltop surrounded by the Redwood forest with the closest neighbor's house a couple hundred yards away.  While we live in a rural area, Silicon Valley is 15-20 minutes to the north and Monterey Bay is 15 minutes to the south, great for business and pleasure. Levi Stadium is 40 minutes away. Motorcyclists will love this location, lots of great day rides to enjoy.
host_about:
Favorite quote: "Good looks, wealth and education are often wasted on the slow. Everything in moderation and moderation is the first to go."

Husband, father, avid downhill skier, motorcyclist, frustrated landscape artist and builder/craftsman, I enjoy creating things and the company of others. Empty twisty back roads, a firm suspension, and a good apex makes my motor rev. Uncrowded steeps covered in feet  of fluffy powder, blue sky, and mountain vistas are my favorite things. Hanging out with friends at our outdoor bar, drinking, eating, talking, laughing, enjoying the evening, reveling in the beauty that surrounds us. 

We offer a private guest suite (1 or 2 rooms), in a quite, beautiful setting. A romantic get-away, relaxing weekend, a place at the bar after a day of mountain biking, a family vacation adventure or whatever you choose, we'll do our best to accommodate your needs and style. Our 70's mountain home

neighborhood_overview: You'll revel in quietness and the natural beauty of the mountains, 10 minutes to the beach, 1 hour to San Francisco. Eden's my name, Hospitality's my game!

Label me a work in progress...

name: Santa Cruz Beach & Hike Launch Pad
description: Calling all Santa Cruz day-trippers! If you want to enjoy all the coast & mountains have to offer - beaches, hiking, biking, dining and shopping - but crave a quieter and less populated place to rest in the evening - this place is for you.
neighborhood_overview:
Scotts Valley is a small, quiet, walkable/bike-able town far enough away to leave behind the hub-bub of traffic and congestion of more populated areas - but with great freeway access to launch daytrips to the North or South.

We have 3 full size grocery markets, drug stores, coffee shops (Peets, Starbucks, cruz coffee), a renowned skatepark and a fabulous seasonal farmers market on Saturday mornings. Though there is not really much "night life" in our fair city - we do have several brewpubs and wineries which offer music and tastings / specialty food carts. Felton also has the Roaring Camp steam train, great hiking and a zip line park as well.

Our neighborhood is quiet and well-kept, with very little thru traffic and our home has several fruit trees and vegetable patches to enjoy seasonally.
host_about: I am a semi-retired Silicon Valley marketing professional who takes any opportunity to hit the great outdoors - which could include anything from picking wild berries in my neighborhood, to trekking the John Muir Trail. Though I am often away from the home, I pride myself on being highly responsive to any issues or questions that arise during my guests' stay.

neighborhood_overview: You'll revel in quietness and the natural beauty of the mountains, 10 minutes to the beach, 1 hour to San Francisco. Eden's my name, Hospitality's my game!

Label me a work in progress...

description: No George Foreman grill here!  This is a full home, with a full kitchen, driveway and yard in a great location. Walk to Rail Trail. We are on the West Side near everything:  Boardwalk, UCSC, downtown, famous surf spots, Wilder Ranch... You can walk/bike to so many interesting places - enjoy Surf City. neighborhood_overview: Nice quiet residential neighborhood, just off Mission so it's close to amenities.   Steamer Lane and Cowells are close by.
host_about: We are both teachers in the area.  We feel fortunate to call Santa Cruz our hometown. There are many outdoor activities to explore and enjoy within walking distance from our home. name: The Joy of Coastal Mountain Living!
description: Plush 2-Bedroom Cottage in the Santa Cruz Mountains, with beautiful gardens and private patio/BBQ, full kitchen, cozy dining and living room. The unit sits in our 10 acres of park like property surrounded by redwoods.  We have our own gardens, fruit orchards, meadows and our own private pond which you can walk around.  Next door is a well known winery and tasting room, and only 3 miles down the hill are the beautiful coastal beaches.
neighborhood_overview:
We are next door to the tasting room for a good local winery, and there are many more wineries in the area. 1 mile up the road is an ecological preserve with great hiking. It is 3 miles down the mountain to a nice beach. The roads around us don't have a lot of cars so the area is great for bicycling. Go north on Highway One and you are at Davenport, an old whaling town with a nice restaurant and another nice beach. Just further north on the coast is Ano Nuevo State Park, where the giant elephant seals raise their babies on the beach each spring. Also close by are Big Basin State Park (unfortunately temporarily shut after the fires), Wilder Ranch State Park, Henry Cowell State Park and many other great parks.

And of course, we are only 13 miles north of the wonderful town of Santa Cruz.

Note that we have 3 other units on the property, but they are all separated by plenty of space.
host_about:
My day job is investing in technology, hosting startup events and I do some consulting.  But my wife and I also have this magical place in the Santa Cruz mountains, in a clearing amongst the redwoods, next to a great winery, and only 3 miles from the beach.   We have our own pond, and we have surrounded ourselves with fruit trees and floral gardens, which we hope you will enjoy.  When we are not around, our caretaker, Ed Olson, takes care of our guests.  

We hope to create a Shangri-la feel for our guests - totally relaxed in the mountains and nature, but with all the comforts of home.  We are also frequent travelers, so we know how important it is to feel at home when staying in new accomodations.

name: Natural Bridges Beach House- Walk to beach & cafes
description:
LOCATION, LOCATION, LOCATION
*BEFORE BOOKING- Use the Contact Host button in the Hosted By section to allow your expectations to be exceeded.*

Located on the beautiful Westside in Santa Cruz, across the street from Natural Bridges State Beach Park, and 1 1/2 blocks to scenic West Cliff Drive. Close to the Boardwalk, Wharf, downtown, UCSC, and prime surfing.
neighborhood_overview: The house is located on a quiet cul-de-sac surrounded by owner occupied homes.   The cul-de-sac is directly across from Natural Bridges State Beach Park and 1 1/2 blocks to the ocean.
host_about: I graduated from University of California at Santa Cruz (UCSC) back in the days when the students adopted the banana slug as the school mascot, there were no grades and Natural Bridges State Beach Park had two natural bridges over the ocean. After four years, I was ready to leave Santa Cruz for life in the big city- San Francisco! I re-discovered Santa Cruz after being gone for almost two decades and planning my 20th college reunion. The timing coincided with the birth of our child. I experienced what the area had to offer and was impressed by the changes and reassured by the familiarity. Santa Cruz is an easy getaway from our San Francisco family home. We find the drive very therapeutic with the transition from our fast paced lives to our Santa Cruz sanctuary. The 75 minute drive to Santa Cruz from San Francisco is beautiful through the evergreens on Highway 17 or by the ocean on Highway 1.

description:
Permit #211346. 100 yards to the beach! Sleeps 6 guests + 4 kids (age 7 & under) Location!!! Family friendly, comfy 1500 sq.ft home: 2 BR + "3rd" Bedroom/liv room w/ pocket doors close for a “3rd” Bedroom. 2 full baths, hot outdoor shower, TVs in Family & both bedrooms, gas & charcoal BBQs, game room w/ shuffleboard, beach toys & more!

*No Parties or animals (owner has asthma & allergies) no smoking anywhere on property
neighborhood_overview: Sunny Cove beach is located in the Santa Maria Cliffs neighborhood in the Live Oak area of Santa Cruz.  House is 100 yards to Sunny Cove. It is one of the best neighborhoods in Santa Cruz!  Many full time residents make it relaxing with beautiful, well maintained homes.  STARBUCKS one block away, there is a great Sunday Farmer's Market across the street, several good restaurants in walking distance.  Mini mart /  Mexican taqueria “Los Periscos Market" just two streets away.
host_about:
Beach home owned by three families that love the Santa Cruz community,  water sports, and all the wonders the ocean has to offer!

We wish we lived here full time but work has us anchored to the other side of the hill for now.   When time allows, we are lucky enough to call this a home away from home.  We enjoy surfing, boogie boarding, sailing, fishing, and just relaxing at the beach with our families.

FUN History:  The house was nicknamed  "Ansel's Getaway" as ANSEL ADAMS was friends with the original owner of the home, John Bei.  Ansel and John would hang out in the basement smoking cigars and discussing leather tanning projects.  At the time, Ansel and John worked together at a local leather tannery shop creating camera cases of course!  According to the Bei grandchildren, Ansel was quite a character and a frequent visitor of the home.  

We have had a few artists visit Ansel's Getaway that have been artistically inspired during their stay.  Their work is displayed at the beach house.

name: Seabright Contemporary Studio
description: Immaculate furnished 500 square foot independent studio. Queen sized bed. Hardwood floors, clerestory windows. Full kitchen with 18" dishwasher. NO  disposal. Near Harbor and Seabright Restaurants.  Bath has shower only. No pets or smokers.  Ten day minimum. The City of Santa Cruz requires any tenant staying less than 30 days to pay a 14% Transient Occupancy Tax, which i must collect in addition to the  rent.
neighborhood_overview:
My neighborhood is quiet and surprisingly, at the back of the yacht harbor which is six blocks away. There are great local restaurants, bakeries and shops as well as the Rio Theater nearby. There is even a Roller Rink, which also has Jazzercise. Pacific Cultural Center is two blocks away, with Yoga and Feldenkrais classes available. The “Bicycle Trip “bike shop rents bicycles and is near by. It is easy to get to downtown, and everything is close by bike. We are not far from eight art movie screens and there are an additional 13 movie screens in town. The Rio Theater and Crepe Place have live music and are a short walk away! The Kuumbwa Jazz club downtown presents world class acts.

DO not leave valuables in your car...there is a lot of pedestrian traffic and you don’t want to invite theft!
host_about:
I love to garden, travel and enjoy good food. I love music ( our local Jazz club, the Kuumbwa is amazing!)  I am also a dancer, and love to move in many ways. Paris, Prague, London, Florence and Sienna are favorite places abroad, NYC , Portland, Nashville are good in the States.

As a hostess, I am pretty hands off... will love to show you on a map, our local farmer's markets, where the good local restaurants are and how to walk to the harbor ( four blocks from the house) and beach. I like things clean and simple; prefer the outdoors or a big city. There is no TV in the house, but a great sound system...I speak French fluently, can get by, barely, in German, Italian and Spanish.

host_about:
Hi I am Sundeep and I live in San Francisco. I am always terrible with these describe yourself things but I enjoy traveling, watching sports, beer tasting and meeting new people. 

My favorite travel destination is Germany but I also like those friendly Canadians and the next place on my travel wishlist is Thailand as I love Thai food. I also enjoy being near water specifically the beach and hearing the crashing of the waves. 

I would make a great host because professionally I work in real estate and know how to manage my properties and make my residents be it short or long term happy. I also love food and am always willing to give a dining recommendation.

My life motto can be summed up in this quote about positivity;

Success is failure turned inside out–
The silver tint of the clouds of doubt,
And you never can tell how close you are,
It may be near when it seems so far;
So stick to the fight when you’re hardest hit–
It’s when things seem worst that you must not quit.

name: Peaceful & Private Seabright, 1 mile from beach
description: 600 sq. ft. home. Attention is paid to every detail, highest quality bed & linens, bbq, large private patio, SUPER PRIVATE & QUIET, one mile from the beach,  walking distance to the harbor,  1 mile from the boardwalk,  5-7 minute drive to UCSC, restaurants walking distance as well as grocery stores. Fully equipped kitchen, 2 bikes, up to 3 occupants max
neighborhood_overview:
Our Seabright neighborhood is a very quiet residential area. We have a small park 1/2 block away from our home, great for kids, and pups!
We also have a legal off-leash dog park, Frederick Street Park, less than 1 mile walk away. The park is right above the harbor, and provides a very large fenced in open space for lots of pups!

We are only 1 mile to the harbor, Seabright beach, the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, and UCSC. Arana Gulch, a 40 acre open space is only blocks away, walk it or ride on the bike path, over to the Harbor, Crows Nest, the beach!
FUN!
We've got an assortment of great grocery stores within walking distance, and lots of yummy restaurants.(Staff of Life, Whole Foods, Shoppers Corner..and there is also Safeway and Grocery Outlet)
The Buttery (yum!) is within a mile away, as is the Seabright brewery, Akira sushi (3 blocks away!)La Posta Italian restaurant, Tramonte..delicious pizza, Lillians Italian Kitchen, Linda's Seabreeze Cafe (breakfas
host_about:
My life motto …CARPE DIEM!
Life is too short, we must embrace one another, eat well, live well, and play hard!!!
You can find me in my garden, hiking with my pups… or cruising the coast on my Elliptigo (stand up bike)..
We love to cook and entertain….. 
The ocean is my sanctuary, and I visit it almost everyday.
If I'm not at the ocean, I'm in the redwoods, hiking a trail, and enjoying the peace and beauty of nature.
Since I've become a host with AIRBNB, I've been honored to meet amazing people, and many I now consider friends.
It's an honor to host, and I'm always looking forward to meeting my next guest!

name: Charming Seacliff Beach Bungalow
description: Welcome to Seacliff Beach Bungalow, an iconic beach house for your coastal getaway! This cozy cottage is 2 BR/1 bath with private outdoor shower. Located 3 short blocks to Seacliff Beach and walking distance to restaurants.
neighborhood_overview:
This quiet Seacliff Beach community is highly sought after, as it is three blocks to Seacliff Beach, home of the Palo Alto, a.k.a. 'The Cement Ship' and Seacliff State Beach. Our home is located in a classic beach community - narrow street, lots of local families and people walking.

Enjoy dining at local restaurants, cafes and deli. Nearby you’ll find a fishing pier, Seacliff State Park Museum, golf course, Forest of Nisene Marks State Park, wineries, restaurants, antique shops and a small movie theater. Other nearby beach communities include Santa Cruz (10-12 minutes), Capitola (5-7 minutes), as well as Monterey and Carmel to the south (45-50 minutes). Aptos is central to each of these locations and surrounded by many wonderful state parks, beaches and attractions, including the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk.
host_about:
currently landlocked californian, but heart always at the coast. love traveling to kauai (our favorite family destination) - the hawaiian islands are so incredibly beautiful and we feel at home. other favorite destinations include australia, italy, lake tahoe and big sur.  favorite restaurant is momofuku in NY, but favorite food hands down is the ahi poke counter at foodland in princeville (amazing selection and great price). 

as a host, want to ensure guests are comfortable and make the most of their stay. my husband and I grew up in the bay area and frequented santa cruz - so we love to share our favorite beaches, activities, restaurants and shops. we are super friendly with our local neighbors so it's important that our guests are respectful and treat our home with care.

name: AptosForestRetreat Hot Tub DIY Breakfast #231294
description:
Come and stay with us, unwind and feel totally relaxed! Hear the birds sing to you, watch the hummingbirds and BREATHE! Venture out the door, walk in our neighborhood and see old growth redwoods. Let your cares drift away with a glass of wine by the fire. Take a soak in the hot tub then wrap up in the spa bathrobes. If you are feeling adventurous you can also hike out your door to Nisene Marks State Park and have a day!
Early arrivals from noon until 4:00 require an early check in fee of $45.
neighborhood_overview:
Our home is located next to Nisene Marks State Park. Our home is in the woods facing south with plenty of sun exposure. You will feel as if you are miles away from the rush of life, although you will only be two miles from the Village of Aptos. You will find a few interesting shops, cafes, wine tasting and a variety of restaurants. You can also walk out your door and be surrounded by coastal redwoods!

The addition of the Hot Springs hot tub requires more cleaning time. The filters are cleaned, pH is balanced and the water is kept at the correct level of chlorination before each new guest arrives. The water will be clear and clean for you, hopefully it will be that way when you leave.

The drive to our home is along a narrow road that follows Aptos Creek, so as a creek will curve so does the road to our home. There are towering redwoods, wildlife frequently cross the road, so please drive slowly and enjoy the beautiful two mile drive!

There are no stre
host_about: Nine years have come and gone since I began this incredible adventure with Airbnb! I feel blessed to be able share my home and gardens. It was not a dream of mine to open an Airbnb, but the idea gave me an opportunity to meet amazing guests! I have created a welcoming space for guests to BREATHE! Come, relax, share your story and add on to your memories!

name: Birdsong Studio by Beach-Jasmine Gardens
description: Jasmine Garden Oasis Retreat House—3 block walk to quiet beaches. Ideal for individuals, couples, or families seeking serenity. SC Permit # 231326. Two upstairs independent guest studios inside our home, each with queen bed and extra beds for $25 charge: Jade Studio with private deck, and Birdsong Studio overlooking garden. Garden hot tub, meditation & QiGong instruction, bicycle loan, allergy-free, healing sessions, and low-EMF option--renewing for heart, body & soul. Sunrise/sunset at beach.
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood is a relatively quiet neighborhood with an assortment of people who enjoy living near the beach--including long-time residents, families, retired people, UCSC students, and surfers interspersed to keep it characteristic of Santa Cruz.
Two blocks away is a modest shopping center which hosts the local farmer's market on Sunday mornings. A handful of eateries and a coffee shop, from fast food to upscale dining, line the two blocks toward the beaches. A back way to the beach (our special secret) is three lovely blocks, two of which are walking/biking trails, one lined with Cypress trees, and the next along a lagoon lined with Eucalyptus trees. Wonderful Farmer's Market across 17th Street on Sunday mornings is not to be missed!
The Harbor and Crows Nest restaurant and nightclub are a several blocks to the west along the shore. Downtown Santa Cruz is 3 miles west and Capitola, a quaint seaside town, is 2 miles east. Both are easily accessible by bike lanes, public
host_about: We, Peter & Marie, are a married couple who relish offering our sweet space & location to guests. We enjoy living in a tranquil atmosphere and want to share this with others of like mind at our home, Jasmine Garden Oasis Retreat House near the Sea. It is a modest home tucked away in a modest neighborhood three blocks from the beach in east Santa Cruz with two independent Airbnb studios upstairs, and expand to include the whole house when we offer guided retreats. We keep gentle gardens and cosy comfortable atmosphere for people who want a time of  renewal for body and soul. Often we enjoy the short tree-lined walk to visit the quiet beach and listen to the surf,  especially at dawn and dusk. We welcome our Airbnb guests to join us early mornings with either QiGong or meditation in the garden or at the nearby lagoon. We have a list of healing artists who have offered to deliver their services to our guests in their private rooms or in the garden.

name: Family Walk 2 beach/West Cliff Wharf View/Dogs ok
description: Pet Friendly. Hot Tub. Views. Walk to several West cliff Beaches~ Steamers lane, It's Beach and Lighthouse field/Surf Museum. Walk to the Boardwalk and Wharf in under 10 minutes.
neighborhood_overview:
You will be able to walk from the front door to West Cliff Drive in under 3 minutes. The wharf is just another 5 minutes, and then you have the Boardwalk and Cowell's beach another couple of minutes from there. There are several wonderful restaurants on the wharf. During the summer months you will find salsa dancing and live outdoor music at the Ideal bar and grill located at the entrance of the wharf. There are also free Friday night concerts at the boardwalk. from June til September.
If you bring your dog there is a great walk the other direction on west cliff towards the lighthouse and surfing museum at lighthouse field. Mitchell's Cove has off leash hours for free running, and Frisbee. About a 10 minute walk to the lighthouse. West cliff drive takes you from the wharf all the way to natural bridges beach.

name: Cozy Seaside Studio - Minutes from the Beach!
description:
Welcome! Coastal Seaside Studio, minutes from the beach, a short, flat stroll along the creek to RDM Beach awaits you. Private patio with BBQ.

Walking distance to Venus Restaurant, Pixie Deli, coffee shop & Sea Cliff Shipwreck.

Fun activities include wine tasting, hiking in Nisene Park, paddle boarding, biking, lounging on the beach, swimming, surfing, bonfire at the beach, dog walking and more!

Not too far from Capitola Beach, Beach Boardwalk or kayaking at Moss Landing.
neighborhood_overview: I love walking down the creek to the beach and the walkway to Sea Cliff Beach Pier and looking out at the Shipwreck. Free admission to Sea World out there and with the birds and everything it's like something out of National Geographic at times.
host_about:
No act of kindness,
no matter how small,
is ever wasted.
   - AESOP

Azores Islands, Portugal - I could be a bit bias here, as my family is from the beautiful island of Pico, Azores. 
I was very fortunate to have backpacked on my own for 9 months all throughout SE Asia, New Zealand, Australia, Nepal and Hong Kong and love every one of these places. It was the best time of my life.

Single mom, woman owned small business owner. 

Thank you for your support!

name: Steps to Beach, Comforts of Home
description: This cozy 1-bedroom in-law unit is just steps to Rio del Mar beach, walking distance to restaurants, and a quick drive to hiking, kayaking, whale watching, wine tasting and more! Full kitchen, wifi, streaming video TV (Roku), beach gear. A maximum of two guests allowed.
neighborhood_overview:
The Rio del Mar / Aptos area allows you to be close to nature while still having all the conveniences of a charming town. It's also a great base for exploring the Central Coast - Monterey and Carmel are just a half-hour away!

From our place you can walk for miles along the beach, and you will often see dolphins, seals, all kinds of sea birds, and even whales right from the shore. You can also walk to restaurants, bars and cafes in Rio del Mar and Seacliff Village, or drive about a mile to find shopping, restaurants, and grocery stores in Aptos Village. Capitola-by-the-Sea, Downtown Santa Cruz, and the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk all just about 10-15 minutes away by car.

Just a little over a mile away there is awe-inspiring hiking among the redwoods at Nisene Marks park. Kayak rentals and whale watching trips are available nearby out of the Santa Cruz Harbor and also at Moss Landing. Drive about 15 minutes from here for wonderful wine tasting in Soquel or Corralito
host_about:
A Bay Area native, my heart has always belonged to the beach! I studied at UC Santa Cruz and in 2014 relocated to Aptos from San Francisco. I love exploring the area on foot with my husband Andy and our dog, Betty - ask me about our favorite walking routes! I'm a fan of the arts and you can often find me watching live music or a dance performance, locally or in San Francisco. 

I look forward to meeting you!

description:

neighborhood_overview:
Located just south of Santa Cruz off Highway 1, Seascape Beach Resort gorgeous accommodations overlooking the Monterey Bay.
The entire resort sits atop breathtaking bluffs overlooking the ocean and beaches below. The walking path in the center of the resort leads down to the beach.
On the resort you will find The Seascape Park, Numerous walking paths, The Sanderlings Restaurant and bar, 3 pools and spas, and a full gym (gym access with additional fee paid on-site).
Across the street from the resort, you will find Seascape Village which offers restaurants, cafes and shops.
The PGA rated Seascape Golf Course is only 5 minutes from the resort.
In the Heart of Aptos just over three miles or 10 minutes' drive away you will discover what happens when the redwoods meet the sea. This idyllic setting is perfect for mountain biking, hiking or exploring the historic village. In the village you will meet the lovely people of Aptos who love their town and its visitors. Pic

name: Harmony & Labyrinth by the Bay
description: Your room with a private en-suite bathroom , queen bed,  heated dual controlled mattress pad below flannel sheets under a large domed skylight. Wifi, private entry via French door from the deck overlooking a lush zenlike garden property with a 22' labyrinth for your meditative walk. Recently added amenities include a mini refrigerator and a classic small microwave. The yard has outdoor tables for dining with guest's discardable food containers and dishes. We do not allow the use of our kitchen.
neighborhood_overview:
Live Oak is an unincorporated mid county area situated between the cities of Santa Cruz and Capitola extending from Pleasure Point at the coast to the village of Soquel! Our home is a 5 minute bike ride from the beach and close to the surfing mecca of famed Pleasure Point breaks and the Yacht Harbor. Close by is the upper yacht harbor entrance to the new bike/bridge path across Arana Gulch that is both scenic and fun.
Santa Cruz is a unique and special place that can revive your spirit quickly, especially here on this beautiful Santa Cruz property!
host_about:
Former California Highway Patrolman and VP of Sales and Marketing for Pacific Cookie Co. Grandfather to ten including now 12 year-old twin grandsons who live in the South Bay of LA. Love the ocean, both in it and on it, gardening, biking, walking in beautiful Santa Cruz, especially along the new E. Cliff Ave walkway or Arana Gulch!
After leaving the highway patrol, I took a path that essentially went from CHiPS to chocolate chips!
Author and Founder of DriversYoga and Nowhere Yoga both 
 are mental technique to keep you in the moment while driving. My guidebook, The Art of Looking Through the Windshield can be purchased from Amazon.
Most say I get along well with being a very genial host.
You can talk to me about Nowhere Yoga!
Over the years we have created a mature and unique garden landscape full of beauty and sound in the mode of a zen temple sanctuary between the cities of Santa Cruz and Capitola. A visual stress remover! Come and experience, we're here for you. A relaxed self download if you will! 
Following the earthquake of 1989 we purchased 8K handmade bricks from the demo site of the downtown Oddfellow's building. (next door to the Cooper House building, now O'Neill's Surf. The bricks were vertical from the date of 1893 to 1989! So while here you are walking on a lot of Santa Cruz history and the building that housed the original town clock!
Airbnb ask me to tell guest if I have a life motto. Well yes in fact I do;  
Flexible indecision with all seriousness aside and forward to the rear"!  "It's always 'the ole same space"
And if you come, welcome to Santa Cruz---The gem of the central coast—-A special place! 
Aloha and Namaste
STORM UPDATE : At 5:12 AM on January 9 during 80 mph gale force winds our 90 ft. heritage Douglas Fir tree was pushed down!
Hopefully by June the ground can support the crane needed to lift this immense weight-tree has 48 inch diameter! Guest can walk thru a cut pass way to the labyrinth. Tree was the tallest on Chanticleer Ave. Also a large sinkhole evolved and repairs are underway!

A Romantic Get-Away!
neighborhood_overview:
We love the neighborhood of Rio Del Mar in Aptos.
Nice walk to the the beach; depending on the time of the year, you can see dolphins migrating back and forth from Monterey Bay to Santa Cruz in the morning and late afternoon.
If hiking & biking 🚴‍♀️ are your cup of tea , Nisene Marks Forest is a great spot, and only 4 minutes from the house.

Blessings to you.

name: Jade Studio by Beach at Jasmine Garden Oasis
description: Jasmine Garden Oasis Retreat House—3 block walk to quiet beaches. Ideal for individuals, couples, or families seeking serenity. SC Permit # 231326.  Two upstairs independent guest studios inside our home, each with queen bed and extra beds for $25 charge: Jade Studio with private deck, and Birdsong Studio overlooking garden. Garden hot tub, meditation & QiGong instruction, bicycle loan, allergy-free, healing sessions, and low-EMF option--renewing for heart, body & soul. Sunrise/sunset at beach.
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood is a relatively quiet neighborhood with an assortment of people who enjoy living near the beach--including long-time residents, families, retired people, UCSC students, and surfers interspersed to keep it characteristic of Santa Cruz.
Two blocks away is a modest shopping center which hosts the local farmer's market on Sunday mornings. A handful of eateries and a coffee shop, from fast food to upscale dining, line the two blocks toward the beaches. A back way to the beach (our special secret) is three lovely blocks, two of which are walking/biking trails, one lined with Cypress trees, and the next along a lagoon lined with Eucalyptus trees.
The Harbor and Crows Nest restaurant and nightclub are a several blocks to the west along the shore. Downtown Santa Cruz is 3 miles west and Capitola, a quaint seaside town, is 2 miles east. Both are easily accessible by bike lanes, public transportation and car.
host_about: We, Peter & Marie, are a married couple who relish offering our sweet space & location to guests. We enjoy living in a tranquil atmosphere and want to share this with others of like mind at our home, Jasmine Garden Oasis Retreat House near the Sea. It is a modest home tucked away in a modest neighborhood three blocks from the beach in east Santa Cruz with two independent Airbnb studios upstairs, and expand to include the whole house when we offer guided retreats. We keep gentle gardens and cosy comfortable atmosphere for people who want a time of  renewal for body and soul. Often we enjoy the short tree-lined walk to visit the quiet beach and listen to the surf,  especially at dawn and dusk. We welcome our Airbnb guests to join us early mornings with either QiGong or meditation in the garden or at the nearby lagoon. We have a list of healing artists who have offered to deliver their services to our guests in their private rooms or in the garden.

name: Pleasure Pt Beach Home/Moran Lagoon View
description: Live like a local in this one of kind sunny, tranquil updated two story 2,010 sqft home which has multiple skylights and decks on both levels.  Backing up to the greenbelt of Moran Lagoon, enjoy the views of the seabirds, monarch butterflies and ducks while listening to the waves.  Perfect for families, romantic couples, work from home, or corporate retreats. Easy check in/check out with door access code. Santa Cruz County Vacation Rental Permit 141245.
neighborhood_overview:
Very quiet neighborhood on a dead-end street, no thru traffic. Houses on our side of this street back up to Moran Lagoon. Beautiful views of green-belt and quick walk to the beach. Enjoy the views of the monarch butterflies and ducks while listening to the waves.

The house is a 5-10 minute walk to several area beaches for a fun day of surfing, boogie boarding, sunbathing, and relaxing. Surfers only have a short walk to enjoy the world class surf at Pleasure Point break, the Hook, 38th, Sharks, and 26.

The restaurants and shopping on Portola and 41st are just a 15-20 minute walk or 10 minute bike ride away (0.9 miles).

Capitola and The Harbor/Crow’s nest are both a 2 mile walk, (Please note they are in opposite directions.) Walking 30-40 minutes, biking 20 minutes, and a 5-7 minutes drive.

The Pleasure Point Market is a short walk away or there are a number of grocery stores within a 5-10 minute drive (Whole Foods, Trader Joe's, Safeway.)
host_about: We are a couple who owns several rental properties in the Bay Area and Santa Cruz.  We love to travel and welcome fellow travelers to our vacation rental home in Santa Cruz.  Some of our favorite things to do when in Santa Cruz is walking the beaches to Capitola during low tide and collecting, shells, driftwood, and beach glass or riding our bicycles all over town. We love traveling throughout Europe and especially Italy.  Our bucket list of near-future travel destinations are Spain, Portugal, Morocco and Ecuador & Colombia.

name: Vacation at Seahaven in Santa Cruz!
description: This cozy 4 bedroom & 2 full bath beach house offers a private fenced back yard with BBQ and a Hot Tub.  Just a 5-minute walk to the Beach and mins drive to the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk and Capitola.  Take in the beach lifestyle in a lovely sanctuary by the ocean.  Enjoy quality family time and relax your cares away!  Close to restaurants, shopping and walking distance to surfing and beach fun!
neighborhood_overview:
Just 1.5 blocks from Pleasure Point! The most amazing spot to watch the surfers, walk the paved path along the beautiful cliffs or do some surfing! The other direction is 26 Avenue beach where you can sit in the sun, watch the surf, take a dip in the ocean, body surf, run the dogs on the beach, or have an evening fire! Bathrooms are located across the street in the parking area.

Just a short 10 minute drive or a long walk to Downtown Capitola! Food, beaches, shopping! Or just a great place for a stroll.

Just 15 minute drive to Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk. Fun under the sun! Games, rides, Miniature Golf, Arcade, or bowling. Walk the pier and see the fishermen bringing in their fresh haul! Great restaurants for all types of taste.

Want to go to a Farmer's Market? There is a fabulous one at Cabrillo College in Aptos just about a 20 minute drive from the house.

How about going to Downtown Santa Cruz and enjoy the color of the area?
host_about:
Our parents purchased Seahaven in 2000 as a home for our families and dear friends to come to enjoy the sights and sounds of Santa Cruz, the beauty of the Monterey Bay,  and and most of all to come together as a family to create lasting memories.  Which it did for us and then some!

We are so pleased to share the love and joy of Seahaven with others.

name: Wonderful House in Pleasure Point
description: Located in the heart of Pleasure Point, our spacious home allows guests to enjoy all that the area has to offer - just a quick walk to surf, beaches, and 41st Ave restaurants and shops. neighborhood_overview:
From the website http://www.santacruz.org:

With colorful surf shops, charming beach cottages, and a shoreline teeming with surfers and beachgoers, Pleasure Point is the kind of quintessential beach community that enlivens Hollywood movies and lures envious tourists to California’s sunny shores. Situated on Santa Cruz’s east end, this seaside neighborhood is one of the most vibrant surf destinations along the California coast. The easy going ‘hood earned its hedonistic name from Prohibition-era shenanigans, but you’d swear it’s because spending a day here is such a joy, no surfboard required!

One of Pleasure Point’s biggest draws is East Cliff Drive, a dazzling waterfront promenade—part of the Monterey Bay Sanctuary Scenic Trail—that winds along coastal bluffs overlooking the sparkling Monterey Bay. Join the parade of beach cruisers, skaters, and board-toting surfers as you enjoy vistas of quiet beach coves and thrilling surf breaks.

You’ll spot a crowd

name: Sunny Corralitos Private Room/Bath
description:
Love to have you visit this small country village. Enjoy our beautiful queen master bedroom and bath with private entrance off a large deck.

So close to beaches, redwoods and towns. So much to do and see, or just relax and do nothing at all!

Santa Cruz County Permit: 181366
neighborhood_overview:
We are located in sunny, Corralitos Village across from public tennis courts and park, around the corner from the famous Corralitos Market (fabulous sausages, local fruits and veggies.)

There are picnic tables in front of the Market where bicyclists and hikers may drop in for lunch or snacks.

A block further are both a tacquiria and pizza parlor. Drop in to eat at their picnic tables or take your food with you as you wander the country roads.

The roads are fairly quiet, flat with the odd hill. You will ride through old and new orchards, go by the berry farms that Driscoll has planted along Corralitos Road.

You may want to stop at Alladin Nursery on the corner of Corralitos and Freedom. They have a unique gift shop, fabulous flowers and plants owned by the same family for several genertions.

name: 1.5 blks to beach hottub firepit The best location
description: Comfortably sleeps 10 people in beds. Entertain in the full sun tropical backyard, BBQ, relax in the hot tub & roast marshmallows in the gas fire pit. Best location in town! 1.5 blks. to Natural Bridges State Park Beach & a 2 mile path along the ocean called 'West Cliff" Less than 10 minute drive to Boardwalk, Wharf, Downtown & Derby park. Large collection of beach, bikes & baby gear for your use. very clean and well maintained.  In a quiet neighborhood, not suitable for loud gatherings.
neighborhood_overview:
The vacation rental (110 Quintana Ct). is located on the lower West side of Santa Cruz. It's a easy close walk to the beach and a 2.5 mile ocean bike/walking path. Located in the most desired part of town. The backyard faces south which means it gets full sun. People love the hot tub and firepit.
Close by to the house is the Swift Street court yard. It's a classy collection of six wine tasting rooms, Santa Cruz Mountain brewery, Kelly's bakery and one of our favorite restaurant's The West End Tap & Kitchen. There are many great supermarkets, restaurants and coffee shops close by.
The neighborhood is not congested like the east side of Santa Cruz and Live Oak. You can park your car at any hour and not have to worry about finding a spot. No permit or metered parking.
Located in a quiet small court. It's more private, less expensive and safer for kids than ocean front homes. You don't have cars and people constantly going by.
host_about: I moved to santa cruz in 95 because of the great outdoor activities. I love living by the ocean and the redwoods. I lived in the vacation house for 15 years and had some of the best times of my life. It's close to the best of Santa Cruz. Once I had my own family I wanted more of the country life. I moved to Bonnydoon located in the santa cruz mountains 15 minutes away.

name: Charming Santa Cruz Haven - Near Downtown & Ocean
description: Welcome to your home away from home for extended stays of 60 days or more. To ensure the perfect fit, we kindly ask that you complete your Airbnb profile. Having past Airbnb reviews is a bonus and warmly welcomed. I leave the calendar open 3 months in advance. If you want a future date beyond that, please contact me. Thanks.
neighborhood_overview:
This is a well cared for space in a great neighborhood, half a mile from UCSC and walking distance to downtown. I am happy to say the neighbors are all really friendly and we often stop to visit with each other. There is a coffee shop just around the corner called The Abbey, which is a great meeting place. Also close to Hwy 1 (Mission St) and Hwy 17 and 1.5 miles from Cowell Beach where you can surf, rent kayaks, or just walk along beautiful West Cliff Drive ..and 3.6 miles from Upper Wilder Ranch and amazing mountain bike trails.
The down hill traffic from UCSC can back up in front of the house as they wait to get onto Hwy 1. This usually occurs in the afternoon and doesn't last that long. The traffic in Santa Cruz in general has gotten a lot heavier in the afternoons everywhere. Since my house is very central, I do a lot of walking and biking. The walk to downtown is literally six blocks and highly recommended. I'd be happy to give any local guidance if asked.
host_about: Santa Cruz local for 26 years and a General Contractor, I'm deeply connected to the Coast and called Big Sur home previously.  My passion is making things, and my home reflects this. It’s your gateway to Santa Cruz's vibrant life: hiking, surfing, yoga, and lively university discussions. Experience more than a hotel stay; let me guide you to the heart of this dynamic place. Your joy in discovering its unique charm is my mission

name: Oceanfront Condo at Pajaro Dunes
description: Charming Pajaro Dunes oceanfront condo. The white sand beach is just a short walk out the front door by panel wood boardwalk through this fascinating complex & the natural habitat of grassy dunes. Bordering the shoreline, it offers a breathtaking ocean view from the living room, master & private balcony. Pajaro Dunes Resort is a secluded, gated community sitting atop the dunes surrounded by the Monterey Bay & natural lagoon. Play or relax all day here!*Ask about our Celebration Package Add Ons!*
neighborhood_overview:
Pajaro Dunes is where the Pajaro Valley meets the white sandy beaches on this secluded strip of Monterey Bay. This expansive gated community stretches along the coast, where this long stretch of uniquely designed buildings have been laid out between the grass shrouded sand dunes and the Watsonville Slough. It is home to a variety of wildlife. Walking paths will lead you in all different directions where you can explore the vast natural beauty of this unique setting. Within this beach community you can take a walk on the wind rippled beaches where you will likely find a white sand dollar or two along the way. You can admire the wildlife sanctuary spotting herons along the lagoon and sea life like dolphins and sealions in the bay. For added activity take on a game of tennis, horseshoes or volleyball as the resort includes use of eight tennis courts and nature trails. As the sun sets build a bonfire and warm up as the night wind cools the air.

name: The Hummingbird Haven
description:
Enjoy the vibrant life here. In your own little oasis, enjoy the hum of Hummingbirds flying outside your window and the beautiful views we offer from your large private patio or from the deck.
It is a wonderful place to recharge, relax or have a retreat.
neighborhood_overview:
The guests that we have had in the Hummingbird Haven & the Mushroom Dome Cabin are amazed by the quiet and peaceful nature of our area. At night, you will hear lots of crickets, maybe an owl or a tree frog and sometimes the ocean waves crashing in the distance. In the summer, you can see the Milky Way as we are far enough away from city lights that, on a clear night, you can see quite a lot of stars.
The Monterey Bay is one of the most vibrate marine sanctuaries in the world - sometimes hosting the largest gathering of marine mammals in the world. We have various whales here year round with whale watching tours daily. Check out our reviews of the Mushroom Dome Cabin to get feedback from our guests of our property. If you plan ahead, you can have a larger group here by reserving both spaces.
We also have a metal geodesic dome climbing structure, a small netted trampoline and a tiny playhouse for kids to play with.
host_about:
We live on 10 beautiful acres of sun, oak forest, redwood groves and gardens with a parrot, 2 cats, a small dog, 12 chickens and from 200 - 500 hummingbirds - depending on the time of year..  

I have been hosting on airbnb since July, 2009 and really love what this company has made possible. I have met so many wonderful people from around the world that I would never have met if I hadn't had this opportunity with airbnb! Some of our guests (especially the ones from Europe) have never seen a hummingbird before and here they get to see them up close - just a few feet from them as the birds "hum" around the feeders.

We welcome you to come experience the peace and tranquility that our wonderful land has to offer.

Distance yourself from the craziness that has become our new normal.
This is comfortably warm space to unplug, read a good book, watch for whales and dolphins or take long walks on a practically deserted beach. Or just go crazy: fly a kite, kayak, paddle board...Our beaches are located 200+ yards away from public entrances. Lot's of room. Very few people.

host_about:

name: Seabright Cottage
description: The one-bedroom cottage is a peaceful retreat, nestled in a quiet family neighborhood, close to all that is Santa Cruz. The sunny living room and private garden are great places to chill. It is a very short walk to Seabright Beach and several excellent restaurants. We provide two beach cruisers, and it is only a mile ride to either downtown Santa Cruz or the Marina. So park your car and have some fun.
neighborhood_overview:
The Seabright neighborhood is perfectly located between the boardwalk and the marina. Both are just under a mile from the cottage. It is warmer and sunnier than the rest of town and therefore called the "banana-belt" of Santa Cruz.

Seabright beach is your "classic beach". The wide sands stretch beneath the bluffs. The facilities are decent with flush toilets and an outdoor shower. Lifeguards keep you safe during the summer season. There are fire rings for evening bonfires.

There are a handful of restaurants in the heart of Seabright, and you are only a mile from all the shops and eateries on Pacific Street, downtown. You are in the middle of everything, yet living on a quiet neighborhood street, perfect for peaceful evenings at home.
host_about:
I love to travel. I've been to 4 continents, 20 countries, 39 states.
I like to count things :-) I take a lot of pictures. I am both a guest and host at AirBnB. I am quiet and respectful.

name: Cozy 3BD Pleasure Point Bungalow
description: Tucked away down a private lane, our home is light & bright with loads of charm, a private oasis with a big lush private yard. Beach, surfing, shops and restaurants all within a 10 minute walk. Capitola village 1 mile away. It's a charmer!
neighborhood_overview:
Pleasure Point is a surfer's paradise! We are just over the line (known as Portola Rd) from the dense vacation rental space. We love it because it means you're just as close but in a quieter, more residential area.

Unlike the West Side, where you're in a much more suburban area, we are just minutes from great shopping and dining so you get the best of both worlds!

Whole Foods, Safeway, Target and Macy's are all just a short 5 minute drive away. Capitola Village is a beautiful 1.5 mile stroll from our house - great for morning walks!

Check out what the SF Chronicle Travel Section had to say about the neighborhood!

Feel like a great cup of coffee and fresh pastry during your morning walk on the beach? Davenport has the best bakery around! Craving a four star dinner to celebrate? Davenport can deliver! Wish to enjoy live music several nights of the week within a two minute walk? Again, this is available within walking distance. Is a wine tasting adventure on your list today? name: Safe, Steps To Beach, Spa, Near Harbor, Pets Okay!
description:
This unique beach house is one block from Twin Lakes beach, the finest one in Santa Cruz! It is a 2-story, designer home with an open floorplan, gridwork of glass to allow in plenty of light and offers ocean peeks.

Originally constructed in 1975 with barn-wood imported from Idaho, it offers an old-world charm and a completely modern interior with all the conveniences. Perfect for families & beach lovers!

Owners may bring their pets for an additional fee of $35/day
neighborhood_overview:
This property in a quiet, sought-after neighborhood is only a block from Twin Lakes beach, perhaps the finest in Santa Cruz. There are a ton of places of interest within walking distance - the upper and lower Yacht Harbor (with well-known eateries like Crow's Nest and Palomar), Pleasure Point for top surfers and Capitola with all its restaurants and shops.

In addition, the Santa Cruz Boardwalk is only 2 miles away, the cute little town of Aptos is 15 minutes while Monterey Bay Aquarium and 17 Mile Drive are a 30 min drive. Carmel and Pebble Beach are just another 15 minutes away.

Hello, I am Rex Solway! I have lived in Santa Cruz my entire life and know the town like the back of my hand. I enjoy traveling, fine dining, photography, and the ocean -- I wouldn't be able to live far from the beach! I am personally dedicated to providing the best possible experience for you and your family, and will do my best to create a unique experience you'll never forget!

description:
There is a $20 fee per night for the additional guest.

The covered porch has a patio table and chair.

We are home to greet you and answer any questions; you will appreciate all the privacy our property offers.

The private room is located in beautiful natural surroundings at a house in Aptos. It's set among 15 acres of private land filled with oak trees. An organic working vineyard is on the property.

The pool house is available to you .

Pets are allowed, must be on leash when outdoors.

My husband and I have an active organic working vineyard on the property. We take care of all aspects of the vineyard and winery. I prefer to view the vineyard chores as a zen-like experience rather than labor pruning and maintaining the vines. 
We produce a wonderful estate bottled Pinot Noir wine.
Our 4 children are grown and living away from home now. 
You will see families of deer, wild turkeys, bunnies and occasionally a coyote on the property.

name: Pleasure Point Beach Hideaway
description: Located in the heart of Pleasure Point and nestled along a hidden creek, this very private beach cottage waits for you and your guests to relax and enjoy a restful stay. All walking distance to East Cliff, Pleasure Point & Capitola.
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is comprised of fairly young people. The empty lot immediately adjacent to the creek and the driveway was once the epicenter and final party place of the famed pleasure point bike race - however, since the last residents moved out the home has since been torn down and the party is held in another part of the neighborhood. Its now an awesome, make-shift dog stop and if you have a doggie, I'm sure they will find it full of smells of the neighborhood dogs. The beach is literally 3 blocks down the road and the sunset walks are a must for everyone on the block - we all grab a glass of wine and head down to the cliffs with doggies in tow. We have a very loving, communal group of neighbors and we all watch out for one another.
host_about:

name: 500 feet from the ocean/Rio del Mar
description: Permit #201264 The Coast Queen is a wonderful house for a pleasant getaway to the coast for the weekend. neighborhood_overview: Rio Del Mar beach is two flat minutes away, as are a few shops. Close by is everything else you might want!

Combined Myriam and Mikey have lived in Santa Cruz for over 35 years. We purchased this property  to have as a getaway for us and our friends, and vacationers like yourself. An extensive total remodel was just recently completed, so all of the appliances, bathroom fixtures, etc are nearly brand new.

This house is a perfect home for a family or 1 or 2 couples to have a relaxing weekend so close to one of the best (if not the best!) beach on the central coast. You can walk this beach for miles in either direction, it is not very crowded, and the weather here is never too hot and never too cold. Rio del Mar feels like a small beach town, yet it is 10 miles to Santa Cruz, and less than 40 miles from the Silicon Valley.

name: quiet room w/kitchen & kitty; blocks to downtown
description: Cozy room with a comfy, queen size bed.  Closet with space to hang clothes.  Shared bathroom with one person: me .  :)  Free use of my spacious kitchen, dining table, living room, gas fire-place, balcony, and large front loading washer and dryer.  Free parking space in a safe, gated lot and Free Wifi.  A few blocks away to the lively Brazilian Woodhouse brewery & kitchen,  the festive downtown-- and a 5 min bike ride to the  historic Boardwalk.   Bonus : a very friendly, snuggly cat.
neighborhood_overview:
My home is in a very convenient location: about a 3 1/2 block walk to the lively downtown area, and across the street from the sunny little River Street cafe that serves wholesome, organic meals till 5pm, as well as the Patagonia Outlet. I am also half a block from numerous eateries and shops, including Shun Feng Chinese Restaurant, Chipotle, Cost-Plus World Market, and Ross-- in case you need to grab anything for the beach last minute-like. The historic Boardwalk is a mere 15 minute bike ride away, (a 30 min walk) and Pogonip is a 5 minute car ride away-- Santa Cruz city's own local, hiking spot in the woods-- with quite a few scenic trails to explore. The latest addition to the neighborhood: the Brazilian brewery and kitchen: Woodhouse: a mere 2 blocks away and boasts live music most weekends. :)

My home is right off the freeway too, so it is extremely easy and quick to get to-- a relief when you are tired and just want to rest instead of drive through numerous maz
host_about: I am an elementary school teacher who loves to stay active-- whether its running along West Cliff, snowboarding during winter, hikes in the local SC woods, dancing with friends, or anything else that strikes my fancy.  My latest passion:  hot yoga! <3

name: 5 Acres Mountain Retreat - 2 BR / 1.5BA
description:
Beautiful, two story, Mediterranean-style home. Private downstairs guest suite (700 sq ft) is available for our guests (2 bedrooms/1.5 baths/living area/kitchen nook). Mountain/Canyon views. Wildlife and tranquility. Lots of nearby restaurants. 5 mins to Capitola / 50 mins to Monterey/Carmel.

Naima will be your hostess at the property.

** Santa Cruz County Hosted Rental Permit #181182 (issued June 28, 2018)
neighborhood_overview:
The immediate neighborhood has sparse housing (minimum parcel size is 5 acres). If you need to get away from the hustle and bustle of the cities, suburbs or even beach area congestion, this is the place to be. Once you are well-rested, there's a variety of interesting things to do and places to eat in the vicinity. We especially like:

* Capitola Beach (4.5 mi) - order a slice of pizza from Pizza My Heart, sit on a sidewalk bench and gaze out onto the ocean and beachfront. There are also numerous restaurants and bars that will keep you occupied. Try Margarita Ville for their great assortment of margaritas and appetizers. Stop off at nearby Gayle's Bakery for some delicious deli food and desserts.

* Pacific Avenue, Santa Cruz (6.5 mi) – what would a visit to Santa Cruz be without a stroll down Pacific Avenue in downtown Santa Cruz? The street is iconic for its progressive nature and rivals Berkeley for honors as the ultimate “left coast” university town. Not exact
host_about: We are Greg and Naima Hyver. We would love to share our home with you in the beautiful Santa Cruz mountains. Get away from the hustle and bustle of the downtown area, yet still be within 5 minutes of it.

name: Hawaiian Beach House-1 block beach-Family Friendly
description:
Beach & Lagoon Front! Views of the ocean from all decks and the kitchen/great room. 3 min walk to the beach. This house is centrally located to everything Santa Cruz has to offer. Two bedrooms, two bathrooms, a spacious layout with a large eat-in kitchen great room, formal dining room, living room with fireplace, along with an outside deck with a fire pit
This house is ideal for family get-togethers.
There is nothing like sitting around the fire and listening to the waves crash on the beach.
neighborhood_overview:
The house is centrally located to all the attractions in Santa Cruz.
Three miles away is the main attraction in Santa Cruz, the California Beach Boardwalk. The boardwalk has rides, events and attractions right on the beach. One mile away is Twin Lakes Beach. There you will find the Yacht Harbor, which offers beach volleyball, kayaks rentals and wonderful restaurants also on the beach. Two miles in the opposite direction is Capitola. Capitola is a quaint beach town, with many restaurants and boutique shops. Pleasure Point, which is a popular surf area and 41st Ave, which is filled with restaurants and surf shops, is 1 mile away.
Santa Cruz is apart of the Monterey Bay, which has endless possibilities for sight seeing. One of the most popular is the Monterey Bay Aquarium in Monterey and Carmel, which is 45 miles away.
Silicon Valley is 30 min to 1 hour away depending on which town you want to go to. The other benefit to the house is the new Levi stadium is 35 minut
host_about: We are the Talbot family. We bought our vacation home when our kids were 9 and 12. We wanted a place we could enjoy the beach, but also share that experience with others like you.  We wanted to embrace the Santa Cruz lifestyle with a beach house-style home.    I was born and raised in Hawaii, and I wanted a home away from home. So the island decor fits perfectly with the house location to the surf, beach, and the Aloha Grill down the street.  Our kids love the bunk beds, and we made one of the rooms into a surfer decor to bring the Santa Cruz surf style to life. The beach, which is a short walk away, was perfect for beach lovers alike.  It has boogie boarding, surfing, great sand for sandcastles, and wonderful views. The beach has no public parking, so it is inhabited by mostly locals and doesn't get too crowded. Also, at night it is a great beach for bonfires.  We hope you enjoy the house!

name: Vintage Creekside Hideaway – Walk to Henry Cowell
description:
Do you love glamping? Our cozy vintage 1948 Boles Aero trailer and its outdoor tub is sheltered by a fairy ring of coast redwoods. In this charming creekside forest setting, you two will be just two blocks from the entrance to Henry Cowell State Park.

Walking distance from Roaring Camp, Fern River Resort, and Felton Guild outdoor cathedral for wedding guests.

TOT Certificate # AB00593
Hosted Rental Permit # 231265
neighborhood_overview:
When staying in our trailer, you two will have easy access to the best Felton and nearby Santa Cruz have to offer!

Henry Cowell State Park: 5 min walk
Monty's Log Cabin, closest bar: 5 min walk
Wild Roots Market, health food store: 15 min walk (2 min drive)
The Grove, best restaurant in Felton: 15 min walk (2 min drive)
Hallcrest Vineyards, closest wine tasting room: 20 min walk (4 min drive)
Roaring Camp Railroads: 20 min walk (8 min drive)
Santa Cruz: 20 min drive via Highway 9
Davenport, closest beach with no crowds: 30 min drive via Felton Empire
host_about:
We are a young(ish) couple living in a 1937 summer cabin in the redwood forest and mountains above Santa Cruz. We have a daughter Lucy, born March 2019. She sometimes joins our travels.

Nate is engine house manager at a local railroad, Brianna is a transportation planner. We love tending vegetables and flowers, sailing, cooking lavish meals, long hikes with our puppy, getting lost, wine tasting (including in a brown bag), reading in the sunshine, and most of all traveling! We've visited dozens of countries all over the world, but are also excited to discover new places close to home.

Some of the most beautiful beaches on the Central Coast are here: deep, wide, quiet, and bordered by beautiful cliff-scapes.

name: Cottage over Mountain Pond!
description: Enjoy a plush one bedroom bungalow with separate living room, full bath, rustic pinewood floors and wall paneling (harvested on property), perched on a hill next to our orchard, with a view of our pond. The unit sits in our park-like property of 10 acres.  We have our own gardens, fruit orchards, meadows and our own private pond which you can walk around.  Next door is a well known winery and tasting room, and only 3 miles down the hill are the beautiful coastal beaches.
neighborhood_overview:
We are in the mountains surrounded by redwoods, meadows and a winery. 1 mile up the road is an ecological preserve with great hiking. It is 3 miles down the mountain to a nice beach. The roads around us don't have a lot of cars so the area is great for bicycling. Go north on Highway One and you are at Davenport, an old whaling town with a nice restaurant and another nice beach. Just further north on the coast is Ano Nuevo State Park, where the giant elephant seals raise their babies on the beach each spring. Also close by are Big Basin State Park (unfortunately shut down temporarily after the fires), Wilder Ranch State Park, Henry Cowell State Park and many other great parks.

And of course, we are only 13 miles north of the wonderful town of Santa Cruz.

Note that we have 3 other units on the property, but they are all separated by plenty of space.
host_about:
My day job is investing in technology, hosting startup events and I do some consulting.  But my wife and I also have this magical place in the Santa Cruz mountains, in a clearing amongst the redwoods, next to a great winery, and only 3 miles from the beach.   We have our own pond, and we have surrounded ourselves with fruit trees and floral gardens, which we hope you will enjoy.  When we are not around, our caretaker, Ed Olson, takes care of our guests.  

We hope to create a Shangri-la feel for our guests - totally relaxed in the mountains and nature, but with all the comforts of home.  We are also frequent travelers, so we know how important it is to feel at home when staying in new accomodations.

name: Zen Garden Sanctuary
description: Catch the soft chime of a bell or lyrical note of water falling on water. Priv. entrance. Priv. bath, Sunny room w/ gated garden. Quiet neighborhood. Walk to ocean. UCSC, Marine Lab, wharf nearby. Wine tasting, pubs and restaurants. bike, hike, surf.
neighborhood_overview:
Located on the far western edge of town, close to everything, but secluded from traffic and city congestion. This west side neighborhood is unique in Santa Cruz.

You will find great restaurants, enjoy picnics on the beach, discover local breweries and wine tasting within walking distance or a short easy drive. There is easy access to good food, weekly farmers market, yoga classes, meditation, hikes and ocean adventures.

Zen Garden Sanctuary is located just steps from West Cliff drive. A coastal promenade offering walkers, joggers, surfers room to move and observe the wildlife of the Monterey Bay.

Westside beaches, the Santa Cruz Wharf, the Light House, Steamers Lane, Natural Bridges State Park, and Seymour Marine Discovery Center are easily accessible by foot, bike or a short drive. Wilder Ranch is nearby with it's miles of spectacular hiking and bike trails and access to the north coast beaches. Downtown Santa Cruz is about 3 miles away, a short d
host_about: Arthur and I love sharing our environment with fellow adventurers. As frequent travelers, we  know what it is like to be on the road for long periods of time. Created  as a personal retreat, Zen Garden offers a peaceful place to return.  Coming home to the embrace of a welcoming, beautiful environment is always the best part of the journey. We offer our guests a safe, gentle place to land, to retreat and to explore–an environment you can enjoy as much as we do.  If Arthur is home, he  is  sure to share a moment with you or a tale of his recent travels around the world building community through rhythm. As a health care practitioner, I work to keep body, mind and spirit in balance. We are both writers and artists and enjoy sharing what we create with our visitors.

name: OCEAN VIEW beach home near Natural Bridges
description: Welcome to paradise!  Our modern home is situated near the Santa Cruz coastline with fantastic ocean views and is several minutes walking distance from Natural Bridges State Beach.  It is equipped with state-of-the-art appliances and midcentury modern furnishings.
neighborhood_overview:
Our house is located on the Westside which is a quiet, friendly and safe neighborhood. Great for family gatherings but it is also an outdoor enthusiast's dream! It is the heart of the local surf culture and the wellspring of the distinctive Santa Cruz vibe.

It boasts some of the most beautiful beaches and coastal views in all of Santa Cruz. It is home to Steamer Lane, a world class surf spot. The Santa Cruz Surf Museum, Henry Cowell Redwood State Park, Wilder Ranch State Park, and 6 wine tasting rooms are also short distances away.

West Cliff Drive which is steps away from the house is the scenic route that travels along the coast. It has a two mile walking and biking path that stretches from the Santa Cruz Wharf to Natural Bridges State Park.

There is something for everyone in and around this house.
host_about:
I am an adventurous traveler and have a pretty cool tag-a-long named Riley, my daughter.  We’ve been fortunate to travel to off-the-beaten places to rock climb, backpack, hike and bike,  and snowboard.  Luckily, the Bay Area offers all of this within a reasonable driving distance!  

Airbnb is my first choice in lodging and we have never been disappointed.  I strive to provide the same experience for my guests and make your experience memorable.

neighborhood_overview:
The house is located 2 blocks from the world class Pleasure Point surf spot. Pleasure Point offers expert to beginner surf. Moran Lagoon beach is a quick 5 minute walk from the house. Walking on the promenade of Pleasure Point is a must do! The path is a great spot to watch the surfers, walk the dog and enough the sunshine! Rock view, located also just 2 blocks away is a picture perfect place to watch the sunset. Pleasure Point is just like West Cliff Drive, only better!

The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk is a quick 10 minute drive from the house and is the downtown shopping area. Capitola Beach is a quick 5 minute drive, but it is also walkable and bikable.

From the house hiking, biking, adventuring is all right there. It is a great jumping off point for all that Santa Cruz County has to offer.

neighborhood_overview: Feel like a local in our neighborhood.  The bungalow is inside the Santa Cruz city limits. neighborhood_overview:
La Selva Beach is a quaint and quiet little village that you will fall instantly in love with! It is centrally located to enjoy lots of wonderful family activities; which include great Golf Courses, Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, Monterey Bay Aquarium, Shopping in Santa Cruz, Aptos, Capitola or Monterey and many others. Not to mention the many, many wonderful local Restaurants and Wineries!

The sweeping views of the entire Monterey Bay and Breathtaking Ocean sunsets await you! The night lights of both Santa Cruz and Monterey are amazing!

Surfing or Fishing anyone? Then bring your board and pole! Manressa Beach is noted for the best waves in the entire Monterey peninsula. It is one of the most popular fishing spots as well. Or take a romantic walk along the beach and collect shells and sand dollars!

name: Santa Cruz Beach house w/ Pool & Spa - Summer only
description:
An oasis in town!
Our family-friendly cottage offers it all for a perfect summer retreat: heated private pool, outdoor spa, large private yard, outdoor dining and salon & office. No TV.
Ideally located in a quiet neighborhood, our house is serene, peaceful & close to all the things we love about westside Santa Cruz and a short walk to the ocean.
This 3 bd-2 bath house sleeps 5 in beds (6 max w/ floor mattress).

PRICE INCLUDES the 11% Transient Occupancy Tax that we pay like hotels to the City.
neighborhood_overview:
This is the best location in town!

Short walk along a tree-lined path to West Cliff drive along the ocean, easy access to several beaches (5mn walk to Mitchell's Cove beach), including the best surfing spots in town (Steamer Lane, Indicator, Cowell's), proximate hiking and biking trails (Westcliff drive, Pogonip). Beginner surfers can learn, rent and play in small waves at Cowell's beach (5mn by car).
Regular bike rentals available close by on Mission Street.
Walking or biking distance to main grocery stores (New Leaf Natural foodstore, Safeway), yoga studio (Santa Cruz Yoga) and to trendy french bakery and cafe (Kelly's french bakery, Companion Bakeshop), local coffee shop (Verve), fancy restaurants (Bantam, ...), breweries, and tasting rooms and a short driving distance to many more restaurants and amenities on Mission Street. We are 5mn driving distance to downtown.
host_about:
We are a French-Californian family currently growing and raising our two boys in Santa Cruz. 
We love nature. We spent most of our free time outdoors playing in the ocean, hiking or riding our bikes and practicing yoga. We also like reading, playing board games, listening and playing music. We enjoy sharing good food, conversation and humor with friends. Remodeled 2nd level full ocean front condo located in Pajaro Dunes a private, gated community midway between Santa Cruz and Monterey, just a few steps from a secluded, immaculate beach.
The condo is perfect for those wanting to ‘get away from it all’, or to enjoy the attractions of Monterey Bay and Santa Cruz, e.g. whale watching, surfing, kayaking, wine tasting, and the iconic Monterey Bay Aquarium.

Relax to the sounds of the ocean and watch pelicans, sandpipers, otters and dolphins; search for sand dollars and seashells or go for long walks on the pristine beach.

Amenities available on sight are 5 Tennis courts, 2 Pickle Ball courts, 1 basketball court, Bocce Ball, Sand Volleyball, Table Tennis, Horse Shoes & a giant Chess Game; equipment is available in Gatehouse for all these activities EXCEPT for tennis.

name: cute cottage walking distance to beach
description: We have a little guest house on our property that we're blessed to share with family, friends, and the airbnb community. We're a 10-15 min walk to our private beach. Close proximity to both Santa Cruz and Monterey, and close enough to San Francisco to explore the city for a day trip.
neighborhood_overview:
We live in the country. Every time I step outside, I'm reminded of this in the animals I see right outside my back door. Deer, possums, hawks, owls, rabbits, mice, snakes, lizards, gophers, coyotes, you name it and you'll see it.... from the cute and awe inducing to the not so sweet and cuddly. There isn't a day that goes by that we don't see at lease one of the above mentioned critters.
Walk down to the beach and you'll be amazed at the shore birds, dolphins, otters, and whales that you can sometimes spot right from shore. We feel so lucky to live in such a magical place where we're constantly reminded of how amazing mother nature is.
host_about: We are a fun loving family who snowboards in the winter and surfs in the summer. We love to travel with our 3 kids, camping, exploring new restaurants, San Francisco, Tahoe, and our little slice of heaven in La Selva Beach.

description: Our inviting, recently remodeled and generously spacious, 1800+ square foot, home is centrally located close to all of the places you'd want to go in Santa Cruz (harbor, beaches, Capitola, and the Boardwalk). Our house is filled with natural light and the layout of the property and beautiful back yard offer privacy and relaxation-perfect  for a couples getaway and ideal for a family vacation to Santa Cruz. You also get to enjoy an awesome, friendly, cat, a beautiful garden and laying hens!
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a very unique mixture of residential and commercial, with a tire shop and a school next door, and two cemeteries nearby (it's a pretty quiet neighborhood). We don't have neighbors on either side (a small, local, tire shop on one side and a school on the other). We are within walking distance of the harbor and Twin Lakes beach (~20 minute walk). I live in Santa Cruz, California with my wonderful wife Katharina and our son Oliver.
