We have one incredibly friendly and mellow cat (Dexter), six chickens and we enjoy spending time with friends--hiking, biking, great home-cooked meals, good wine and beer, and generally enjoying all that life has to offer.

We have a passion for travel--nothing is more exciting then finding yourself in a new and unfamiliar place with nothing to do but explore and interact with new people!

We are also extremely responsible people. We own our home and take great pride in having a place that is clean, comfortable and inviting. As guests in other people's homes, we feel the same responsibility and respect for their space.

3 mile running loop:  start from cement boat wharf and run North to cliffs at New Brighton Beach and return.

Use outdoor shower upon return, if necessary.

Capitola:

Take Hwy 1 North one exit to “Park Avenue”.  ~ 3/4 mile

Left at Exit (West”) onto Park Ave.  Follow Park Ave until it ends at Monterey / Bay Road.

Left onto Monterey down hill to downtown Capitola (good luck parking!)

Other Attractions:
Simpkins Pool: Huge public pool, fun pools for kids.  Take 1 North to Soquel and head west on Soquel. Take frontage road south until it hits 17th.

Monterey Bay Aquarium. Head south on 1 until you see signs for downtown Monterey and aquarium.

513 Seacliff Drive, Aptos:  Nearby rest

name: Stay-cation at Serenity
description: This three bedroom two bath standalone consist of a two bedroom home and a separate guest bungalow, is ideal for extended family or multiple family gathering! Only minutes walk to Seacliff State Beach where you can spot dolphins and the occasional whale right off shore. Explore the nearby cities of Capitola, Santa Cruz & Monterey. Enjoy the outdoor BBQ, the fully stocked kitchen or just a quiet evening in front of the wood burning fireplace. Keeping warm while stargazing by the outdoor fire pit.
neighborhood_overview:
Serenity is located in the quiet beach community of Aptos.
- A short 2 minute walk to Beachgate path which leads down to the Seacliff beach! A Parking Pass is available so you can take beach gear, cooler, etc down to the beach.
- A 10 minute stroll brings you to local favorites of Marianne's Ice Cream, Manuel's Mexican food and Ambrosia India Bistro.
- A short drive to downtown Aptos and you'll find Aptos Street BBQ with live Blues, great BBQ and over 30 craft Beers on tap.

name: Private Suite in the Redwoods with a View
description:
Our location is on a quiet dead-end street in the beautiful redwood forested mountains above Felton. We have an intimate private suite (bedroom with Queen bed, sitting room and bath), with its own entrance.

We have a wide view of the San Lorenzo Valley, and are only 2 miles from downtown Felton. Access to hiking, mountain biking, coast trail and surfing is within minutes.

We are taking the current coronavirus situation very seriously, and have implemented advanced cleaning procedures.
neighborhood_overview:
Our place is great for hiking and enjoying the redwood forest. We are just a couple of minutes from Henry Cowell State Park, Big Basin State Park, and Roaring Camp Railroad. We have hiking access to Fall Creek with no need for driving. We are also just a short drive from Santa Cruz beaches and the Boardwalk, as well as coastal trails and whale watching at Wilder Ranch State Park. You’ll love our place because of its quiet location with little traffic, and a wonderful view of the San Lorenzo Valley.

We're only 2 miles from downtown Felton, where you can find grocery shopping, a brewery, and several great restaurants. Within a couple of miles you can find Mexican, Chinese, breakfasts, burgers, Cal cuisine, Italian, pizza, and sushi. Felton is also home to a well-known and very cool international music venue, as well as an excellent coffee house.
host_about:
After 20 years in marine biology I changed careers to being a custom furniture designer/maker. I'm also a semi-pro photographer.

My wife, Sally, works for an international scientific instrument company, and is an avid painter and gardener.

We love to travel whenever we can.

name: Tranquility Base Redwood Mountain Tree House
description: This 85 year old remodeled cabin is in Felton, close to Roaring Camp Railroad, Loch Lomond Rec Area, Henry Cowell's State Park, Mount Hermon Conference Center, Felton Covered Bridge Park. neighborhood_overview:

nail salon, fine coffee roasters, donut shop, USA bank, Metro bus stop. Across the street is Felton Covered Bridge Park with picnic tables, a playground, a big grass play area, and the San Lorenzo river running under the tallest covered bridge in the United States. (Guiness Book of World Records). All along Hwy 9 there are more restaurants, shops and Wild Roots Market Organic Mkt, Rite Aid, Post Office, auto repair, liquor store, banks, the Big Foot Museum, Henry Cowell's State Park. Felton Music Hall.
host_about:
I was raised in Northern California. Having just closed out an electrical business
that I shared with my husband for 40 years, I can now devote my time to creating
a fun, unique place to rejuvenate the soul under the beautiful redwoods of the Santa Cruz Mountains. The Golden Rule is how is how I roll. Travel to Scotland, Tahiti, and to experience the Northern Lights may be in my future.

name: CasaLita Seabright Santa Cruz with Sauna
description:
In the Heart of Seabright!! 0.5 m to the Beach, the Harbor, the Boardwalk (0.6m), Seabright Brewery, Betty's Burgers, La Posta, Verve Coffee, Aldo's, and the Crow's Nest. 5 mins from downtown.

One glimpse will reveal that you are in for something special. A Comfortable Home designed with care and attention is the spirit of Indoor-Outdoor Living, including a delightful Tree-House, sauna, We provide 3 Bikes, surfboards, paddleboard, ping pong, BBQ, fire-pit, hammocks, and More.
neighborhood_overview:
Seabright neighborhood is very unique in some important ways, fast is becoming a mecca of hipster chic, thanks to its bike shops, home furnishing stores, cafes, restaurants and sweet live music venues. As for the laid-back Seabright neighborhood, with its clutch of bars and eateries Seabright also serves as the entryway to Seabright Beach, a long sandy beach between Santa Cruz Harbor and the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk and a
popular spot bonfires. The area has a lively nightlife scene with bars and breweries featuring live music, open micas and karaoke. There are also several neighborhood restaurants, shops and businesses.
host_about:
We are world travellers ourselves. Along with our three children we have travelled around the world. We love decorating and improving our home, and love living in it. We enjoy people and love to share our local knowledge with guests. We enjoy inspiring and being inspired by the friends we make. We live close to most a beautiful ocean and beaches and love to get in them everyday! From kayaking, stand up paddle and traditional surfing, cycling, hiking, and photography, we do it all. The focus is fun and we will put you in the right place to maximize yours.

Meeting people from around the world and travelling are our passions. We also enjoy sharing our home with others so they can experience our bit of paradise in special unique ways. We love hosting travellers because we think our home, and the area where we live in, gives visitors a true sense of what it's like to live where we do. Come experience our home as your home. Like a Local! We want to make your stay as enjoyable as possible. We look forward to hosting you soon!

name: Garden Oasis Guesthouse Relax, Surf & Adventure
description: Welcome to our Artistic Garden retreat! Centrally located in the heart of Santa Cruz, 1 mile from Sunny Cove Beach and Pleasure Point. Close to the boardwalk, yacht harbor, Downtown Santa Cruz & Capitola. Detached guesthouse & spacious lush yard,  fully furnished, outdoor area and more. Our 1/2 acre farmhouse lot is a garden oasis with lush palms, proteas, bamboo & succulents weaving throughout. Our garden and private lot have it all! 1 night stay ok when available just ask.  No animals allowed.
neighborhood_overview:
Our Farmhouse was built in 1932 during a thriving area for Live Oak as the crown jewel of hens and egg production. The chickens are gone but their history has left us with rich fertile soil where we have taken advantage of this resource to plant a flourishing garden.

Live Oak and Santa Cruz raised the second most number of chickens in the State after Petaluma, in the heyday of egg production in the first half of the 20th century. Chanticleer Ave is named after the Chanticleer Rooster, and Live Oak was the epicenter, being the location of the local Farmer’s Exchange, an enterprise modeled after the mid west member-owned Co-ops. Two trains a day brought ingredients for chicken feed to the Exchange and they were milled and blended into feed for the members.

Live Oak is rich in history and we welcome you to explore our quiet neighborhood and discover all kinds of wonderful hidden gems.
host_about: Greetings! We look forward to travels and adventure.

neighborhood_overview: Sidewalks & streetlights. Great coffeshops & restaurants right down the hill.
host_about:
My door is always open to the traveler Job 31:32

Hello to anyone reviewing my home. I hope we will meet you soon. COVID has changed everything. I have only just now re-opened. Welcome back. Prior to the shutdown, we hosted happy travelers from 23 countries, were super hosts and had many positive reviews. 

For those of you traveling into Santa Cruz County.... our home is centrally located and close to highway one and the beach. Occasionally, there may be some freeway noise. 

My rooms are on the second floor, up stairs. My doorway requires a step up of four inches. Therefore I have to say my home is not very accessible at all. We HAVE accommodated a gentleman who just had knee surgery, and two guests with canes, who took good advantage of my staircase bannisters. 

My home is in a neighborhood with streetlights and sidewalks, and I have a very long driveway so you can park off the street.
Spring is upon us, and the days are crisp and sunny, reaching 80’s and low nineties. My home has no air conditioning, but it’s almost always a comfortable temp. The nights are in the 40's and 50's.

The beaches are very occupied, and the tourists and events are back thankfully, so our community has returned to its full and busy feel. 

We are doing our best with COVID. 
Hope to be hosting you soon. 
Peace to all and safe travels.

description: Sunny, airy, private and pet-friendly La Selva Beach in-law studio under a mile to the beach.
neighborhood_overview:
La Selva and Manresa beaches are less than a mile from the studio. They are known to be sparsely populated (wonderful for contemplative sunset walks) with wide sandy beaches, big waves and strong rip currents. They are great places for roasting marshmallows over a beach bonfire, long walks, surfing, boogie boarding, skim boarding, surf-fishing, dolphin watching, etc. Otherwise, our village is a sleepy, family-oriented beach neighborhood. We appreciate guests who will respect that atmosphere.

New Brighton, Seacliff, Palm and Sunset State Beaches are all within a 10 minute (or less) drive as is The Forest of Nicene Marks State Park. The Seascape Golf Club (public, 18 holes) is a 5 minute drive from the studio and Seascape Resort is nearby -- a great site for weddings and corporate events.

Kendall & Potter was established as a real estate company over fifty years ago. 
The brokers Skipper Kendall and William Potter moved to Aptos to fulfill their dream of working in a small town in Santa Cruz County. They soon expanded their services to include property management and relocation to Santa Cruz County along the Monterey Coast.

name: Luxury Country Apartment with Beach Access.
description:
Stay with us and hear the ocean sounds from your rooms.
Our 5 Star apartment is a spacious, totally self contained private area with it's own side entrance attached to the main house.
It is over 610 square feet with 4 separate rooms and French doors leading to our back garden with areas to relax.
We are a short walk to the beach along Monterey Bay. By car you will be half way between Santa Cruz and Carmel by the Sea for shopping, dining or entertainment with many beaches to visit in between.
neighborhood_overview:
We live in the countryside area of La Selva Beach, California just south Santa Cruz over looking the picturesque and famous Monterey Bay.
It is a rural farming area with strawberry fields and miles of sandy beaches.
We are blessed with very friendly neighbors who are part of our neighborhood organizations including bi-annual community meetings, daily internet communications and even our own water company.
host_about: Carolyn and I love our Mission style home, which I built, overlooking Monterey Bay. Building the house was my retirement dream, after a 27 year career in Special Education. I was proud to create a successful program to support  18 to 22 year old autistic and other neurodivergent students. This Adult Transition Program was the first in Orange County focused on integrating these students with their peers at Orange Coast College. My staff and I helped each student, with creative job development,  individually tailored to their strengths, interests, and talents, to find work that many sustained for decades. Prior to creating this Adult Transition Program, I was the director of a school for neglected and delinquent group-home teenagers in San Francisco. Carolyn and I were college sweethearts many, many years ago, at a small Quaker College  in Indiana (Earlham). We stayed friends through marriages, raising our families, and rediscovered our love for each other after losses. Carolyn is a Psychologist and Coach, with a private practice using the Enneagram as a tool to support individuals, couples, business leaders and creatives in their growth, and the integration of head, heart and hands, to become all that they can be.  Her first career was as a Spanish Bilingual teacher in San Francisco, while Bob was working with younger students in residential treatment at ClearWater Ranch in Anderson Valley, California. We've been so happy to discover that we each maintained interests in photography, travel, hiking, snorkeling, swimming in wild waters over all the years, and are thrilled to do so together in this reignited relationship. We also enjoy playing tennis, hiking the many trails here and in Marin County, and sharing each other's friends and family. We were both psychology majors in college, where we first worked with underserved populations. We have a photo history of coast to coast adventures from the past, and we're adding more, now.

name: Country French Beach House
description: Our colorful , Country French Beach House allows you to enjoy the ocean view from the upper decks.  Relax with your choice of stereo, CD player and DVD , and TV on our comfortable leather couch and side chairs.  French Doors open out to front/ back decks to create an inside out feel..  Three of four bedrooms have their own decks.  No common walls between bedrooms, for your privacy. Charcoal /gas grills. Lounge furniture on decks.  Party lights on on back decks  for nighttime chats.
neighborhood_overview:
Our home is located on one of two main arteries that lead directly to the to the water. It is on a hill and is a short 6/10 of a mile to the water downhill (of course its uphill to get back home). The neighborhood is mostly residential with houses on each side being permanent residents.
I don't recommend walking to the beach with little ones. Like most beach neighborhoods there are no sidewalks until you get to the flat area, so if you are taking little ones to the beach I'd recommend driving. There is public parking at the beach.
host_about:
I am a happily retired Marriage and Family Therapist.   My life therefore has been about relationships that matter. 
     I am a photographer.  I love travel and color and the combination of both is  ideal for me.  
     I love hosting couples, groups of women as well as their family members. I g love their complete immersion into the pleasure of our home and its' surrounding areas.  I love my reviews when people "get it" when it comes to our  beach home.  It's fun to hear they spent time trying to imagine the stories that went behind each segment  of decor.    I LOVE France, and then Italy, and Morocco.  Canada is up there too, because they speak French (even though I don't). 
    I also fancy myself a chef (colorful, tasteful, healthy food).   Don't forget to check out all the cookbooks and international magazines.   You will know that I love cooking when you see our custom designed kitchen, the myriad of cooking utensils, french door refrigerator, Viking Stove and Bosch Dishwasher.   The french doors off the dining area open out  to extend your eating areas and invite you for morning  a cup of coffee outside.   The french doors off the living room invite you to watch the fog roll away under the palm tree.  This is yet another thing I love. 
       Walt and I have been married for 35 years.  He is still in practice as a psychologist and has taught mindfulness meditation for about 30 years.  He is the quiet type but rarely sits still.
     Interior design with elegance, color, history and a sense of whimsy would well describe another of my passions.  I like changing things up from time to time so my return guests get to do it all over again.  I love exploring our area for new things for us to do as well as always keep it fun for our guests and their children.  As nice as the house is I encourage everyone to get out there and enjoy  the outside and outlying areas as well.  Nicene Marks is almost within walking distance   The beach is a short stroll.
        I like establishing a relationship with my guests before they arrive, so I know what they need and they know what I appreciate in a guest.  People ask me, "how can you let strangers come in to this lovely home"?  Oddly, its not a problem.  To me our home is not a typical rental.  It is a shared lovely home and I think my guests understand that and feel honored to be there.  They want to maintain our relationship and so do I.
     You will get a feel for my passions as you sit on the couch in front of the fireplace, or on one of the many decks and peruse the books on design, photography, cooking and sweet novels that take place on or near the beach.
  I say to you welcome, come be an honored guest.  Wouldn't like to be my "first" Air bnb guest?

neighborhood_overview: Mt Hermon is a small community near Felton, just a 10-minute drive to Santa Cruz.  Because the home is located in a rural, forest setting it can be a little challenging to find.  If you follow the directions exactly you will be able to find the house easily.  The speed limit in Mount Hermon is 15 mph and this limit is enforced by several nasty speed bumps throughout the village, so keep your eyes open for those.  The terrain is hilly with lots of trees.  A creek runs through the valley and can be accessed for wading and water play.  Mount Hermon Association offers a world class zip line course through the redwood canopy.  Hiking trails throughout.  Roaring Camp steam train ride through the redwoods.  Henry Cowell Redwood Park offers views and a self-guided tour of ancient redwoods. Safeway grocery store, CVS drug store, and restaurants a mile away.
host_about: My husband and I love to travel and we also bicycle on our travels.  We write reports with photos about our experiences along the way. neighborhood_overview:

This lush and forested region is a nature lover's dream, featuring towering redwood groves, hiking and biking trails, and pristine state parks like Big Basin Redwoods State Park. The Santa Cruz Mountains also boast a thriving wine scene, with vineyards and wineries producing exceptional varietals. It's a place to unwind, disconnect, and find solace in nature's beauty, making it a perfect retreat for those seeking tranquility and outdoor adventure.

name: Snug and Cozy between the Skyline and the Sea
description:
Super private, peaceful, and quiet; an excellent place for the traveler who is excited about exploring the Santa Cruz mountains and coast.

Completely private In-law unit with extras needed to make it cozy. Snuggled between Scotts Valley, Felton, and Santa Cruz it's near Henry Cowell Redwoods State Park, 1440 Multiversity, and Mount Hermon Conference Center yet less than an hour from Silicon Valley.

The Airbnb cleaning handbook is followed making this one of the cleanest places you’ll stay at!
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood feels rural, but you're only about a mile from grocery stores, drug stores, restaurants, and a movie theater. Scotts Valley is home to 7 coffee houses. Our favorite, Cruise Café, is just over a mile away. They roast their coffee locally, and the bakery yummies are made onsite.

You're also less than 1/4 a mile away from the hiking trails of Henry Cowell Redwoods State Park. If hiking is your passion, you found the right place to stay! Several former guests have left annotated maps indicating their favorite trails. Feel free to borrow them for your hiking pleasure.
host_about: My husband and I love to travel and getting to know the people who live in the communities we're visiting. If I'm not home I'm usually out hiking in the nearby mountains. I hope you enjoy your stay at my home!

name: Redwood Pine House in Mt. Hermon
description:
Redwood Pine House has a main house with two bedrooms (1 King bed and one bunk bed) plus a full bathroom, plus a guest house (1 Queen bed and 1-3/4 bath). The sunny front deck has outdoor chairs and end tables, so you can enjoy your coffee outside in the morning, or relax in the coolness of the evening.

There's a private patio in the back, with an umbrella, dining table and seating for 6.

Note: The main house and guest house are both included in the rental and are not rented separately.
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is quiet and the neighbors are lovely.  You'll meet and greet people walking the streets, enjoying the trails and shopping in downtown Felton.  There's a great organic market, Wild Roots, plus a large Safeway and CVS Pharmacy for your convenience. Felton's Farmer's market has the finest produce and flowers available; open Tuesdays starting in May; ends in October. Sushi San, Empire Grille and the Cowboy Bar & Grill are local favorites. Check out Wyler Space for unique menu offerings and even catering (check wylderspace.com for hours).  There's lots to do in and around Mt. Hermon, Henry Cowell State Park is open for walks amongst the stately Redwoods, and the Santa Cruz Boardwalk is a quick 20 minute drive down the hill.
host_about: Tim and I live in Manhattan Beach and our two daughters went to University of Wyoming.   Kim has been coming to camps at Mt. Hermon since she was in third grade, and we've continued that tradition with our family.  Tim and I enjoy North Lake Tahoe and we just went to Paris France and London with our daughters.  And yes, we stayed in VRBOs.  Loved it!  Which inspired us to try Airbnb.  We loved the homes, how well they were taken care of by the owners, and we loved living in the area versus a hotel.  Hope you like Redwood Pine House as much as we do!

name: Felton Forest Cottage Near Henry Cowell State Park
description: Your new weekend retreat! The Cottage is situated on unique forest-farm acreage across the street from Henry Cowell Redwoods State Park, surrounded by redwood fairy circles and a beautiful stream. Charming, private, and yet handily walkable/drivable to parks surrounding the town of Felton and the Santa Cruz Mountain area. About 1 hour south of San Francisco, we're a quick 14 minute drive down picturesque Highway 9 to downtown Santa Cruz and it's popular beaches and Boardwalk.
neighborhood_overview: Located in the Bigfoot Hill area of Felton (yes, by the Bigfoot Discovery Museum!), the Cottage enjoys easy access to the main entrance of Henry Cowell State Park - and the beautiful San Lorenzo River - across the highway from the property, with the Felton Guild a couple blocks away. It's within easy walking distance to local restaurants and shops. Roaring Camp Railroad, Fall Creek, Big Basin State Park, and Loch Lomond Reservoir are near by and open for a variety of hikes, bike rides,  and activities.
host_about: Rebecca and Tad have been married 20 years, circling the world many times as proud global citizens, but with deep roots in Santa Cruz. Rebecca is a 4th generation Californian who enjoys traveling with her family, chicken wrangling, gardening, and home improvement. Tad works in the gaming industry, loves movies and making models. They enjoy every minute of life in the forest, and are happy to be able to share their wonderful slice of Felton with others!

name: The East Room @ Redwood Croft
description: In the Santa Cruz Mountain environs of UCSC, we are above North Coast beaches, surrounded by lush coastal redwoods and rural quiet.  "Town" is a short drive - restaurants, pubs, entertainment.
neighborhood_overview: No sidewalks, but plenty of beautiful walks.  The "center" of our Neighborhood is the country school and church - school bell chimes through the arbors on weekdays.  On Sunday Morning, the little Church bell calls. 2 mi walk to the Beauregard Vineyards and tasting room.  Close-by Bonny Doon Ecological Reserve is 200 acres of both easy and challenging hikes.
host_about:
I am artistically inclined, in fact the property is my "canvas" -- I am very dedicated to living with respect for nature, and  admire brilliance wherever I  see it. I have worked with a jazz trio as a singer around Santa Cruz.  I love dogs for the amazing qualities they've developed through eons of living close to humankind.  I am married to Dale, and we have raised 3 children.  
-- I get a kick out of people having a good time at our place, interested in such a variety of things, coming together serendipitously at Redwood Croft.  Of course, quiet retreats are invited, too. This could be my motto:  "Stay open; Stay responsible."

name: Boardwalk Retreat+Hot tub+Bikes+Surfboards+Kayak
description:
Beach cottage in a quiet cute neighborhood, walking distance to the ocean, Santa Cruz Boardwalk, West Cliff Drive, Steamer Lane, Cowell's Beach and biking distance to downtown Santa Cruz. This two bedroom (plus bunk room), home is good for those looking for a clean, peaceful, comfortable place to stay. Surfboards, Bikes, and a Kayak for you to use!

name: The Beach house
description: This traditional 2 bedroom beach house is cozy and comfortable. Located in the desirable Pleasure Point Area. Experience Santa Cruz from this world renowned surf location and one of the most popular local surf spots! Our street is a popular street. neighborhood_overview:
Pleasure point is a small beach community. A world renowned surf spot. Home to the inventor of the wetsuit, “ Jack O’Neil “. Location of the movie “ Chasing Mavericks”
The Beach house sits 3/4 of a mile from the Beach. It’s a nice walk through the neighborhood to the end of the street where it dead ends at East Cliff Dr. which is a popular walking path along the ocean cliffs where you can watch the surfers. When the tide is out there are several small beach areas.
There are several great restaurants along 41st Ave and Portola Dr. all within a mile.
There is a New Leaf Market, and Whole Foods market, Trader Joe’s, lots of shopping, movie theatre and 2 different fitness centers all within a mile.
There is a nice park a couple blocks away with basketball, tennis courts, and children’s play area.
Just a little further away at approximately 1.7 miles to the south is the Capitola village. A sweet little beach with fun shops.
The Santa

description:

host_about: Hey, I'm Michael.    I am a chef  and have lived in the Monterey Bay area for 25 years.  Moving from busy Manhattan where I trained at the Culinary Institute of America, I have embraced the tranquility of this coastal paradise. I love experiencing the outdoor wonder of this area. This area is not only beautifully scenic and full of adventure, it is a place where you can find serenity.  Whether you are breathing in the fresh, ocean air at the beach, paddle boarding on the water, hiking in the mountains, enjoying a glass of local wine, or talking with friendly locals, I know you will, like I have, find restoration and renewal here. name: Charming, Light-filled House  Walk To The Beach
description:
Permit # 231282
Get cozy and comfortable in this charming, sun-filled beach house. Walk to the beach! Enjoy all that the quaint town of Aptos has to offer. Connect as a family and spend quality time together - play board games, cook meals using the full-service kitchen or BBQ grill, listen to the waves out on the deck, have dinner/drinks under the stars, or stream movies on one of five flat-screen televisions - free Netflix. Walk to popular Seacliff Beach to unwind and enjoy the ocean breezes.
neighborhood_overview: Safe and friendly neighborhood, lots of folks walking their dogs and enjoying the ocean air.
host_about:
Hello! 

Welcome to my Aptos beach house. A little bit about me...

I spent 15 years living and working overseas with my family in Morocco, Lithuania, and Costa Rica. I returned to California in 2015 and fell in love with Aptos and the Monterey Bay for its beautiful beaches, mountains, and access to the San Francisco Bay Area. As a beach lover, surfer, runner, and hiker, I found Aptos to be the perfect spot to enjoy nature, the beach, and the mountains all with having quick access to San Francisco to see a Giant's baseball game or to head into Oakland or Berkeley for Ethiopian, Greek, or Indian food, to see a show, or hike in the hills. 

I love adventure travel and do most of my traveling with my kids so I understand what parents are looking for in a vacation - ease and simplicity, memory making, less time in the car and more time doing fun things together, etc.  I believe that showing children the world as often and as early as possible is important. 

“Travel is fatal to prejudice, bigotry, and narrow-mindedness, and many of our people need it sorely on these accounts. Broad, wholesome, charitable views of men and things cannot be acquired by vegetating in one little corner of the earth all one's lifetime.” - Mark Twain

I hope you enjoy my beach home and hope that you are able to explore, learn, enjoy life's simple pleasures, and make lasting memories there.
Warmly,
Sarah

neighborhood_overview:
The house is in a rural valley within a short drive (apt 10 minutes) to several beaches. Unlike our sister beach and boardwalk in Santa Cruz which gets packed with tourists, our closest beach -Rio Del Mar - is miles long and frequented by locals. Great place to go for a stroll, take the stairs to wonderful ocean views, hold a bbq and check out the amazing half sunk ship.
We're also close to renowned hiking under a canopy of massive redwoods at Nisene Marks park, local farmer's markets with fresh organics and home made delicacies. For folks who want to eat out, there are some terrific restaurants and the famous Aptos BBQ, for ribs and live blues.
host_about: Friendly and conscientious, Film Professor in Berkeley. I like to swim, hike, read and cook. I enjoy relaxed family time with my husband and son. Both my husband and my own family are European and we travel quite frequently.  We are multi-lingual - fluent German, French and some Spanish.

name: Sun Savvy ~ Just Steps to the Beach
description: Located on a quiet 'no outlet' street....steps to the sand and one of only 9 World Surfing Reserves! Resident only traffic makes this an idyllic neighborhood...you can even hear the waves break. Two lagoons with nature trails and a very large beach are a few minutes walk.
neighborhood_overview:
What you find in walking distance (1-2 km)
~ Quaint beach village, wharf, cliffs & coves.
~ Picturesque yacht harbor with watercraft rentals.
~ Sand volleyball courts, free beach parties with
live bands.
~ Restaurants offering fresh seafood, views, and a
dozen international cuisines plus micro-brewery
pubs.
~ Weekly local farmers market, Trader Joes,

food markets, award-winning coffee bistros.

host_about:
Growing up surfing brought me to Santa Cruz.....and I never left. 
I won't live without clean air, pure water, art & Nature. 
A bit uncompromising yet spending a lifetime self-employed has, more or less, allowed me to live on my own terms. 
I was a retail merchant of beachwear & skateboards, transitioning into manufacture of skateboards/wheels and sponsoring the 1978 World Champion Downhill Racing Team.

The next two decades, I turned an avocation into a vocation, as a wine wholesaler. 
Then followed another decade as  a  producer and marketer of  an artisanal California extra virgin olive oil, which the LA Times twice nominated as one of the 'Top Five Calif. Olive Oils of the Year'. 
Lately I have been managing a private sports lodge in North Lake Tahoe.

neighborhood_overview:
The Pinecone Treehouse is located in Bonny Doon which is known for lavender farms and wineries and is approximately 10 miles north of Santa Cruz, and inland from the town of Davenport. Coastal redwoods sit inland from Bonny Doon State Beach, where sandhill habitats and trailside plants attract hikers and outdoor enthusiasts. Although Bonny Doon is flavored with an artistic, eclectic flair, it maintains its small-town feel and is a welcoming stop off scenic Highway 1.

Explore the many surrounding Santa Cruz mountain towns as well as local sights which include many local places of interests, trail heads, wineries as well as the neighboring UCSC college campus. Here are a few destinations and their proximity from the Pinecone Treehouse:

Downtown Santa Cruz 15min

Engfer Pizza also nearby and for the coffee connoisseur, you have to check out Verve Coffee.   Days Market located next to Tramonti's, is a quirky little market that has been there for well over 50 years, and has a little bit of everything.   Personally love to walk to the harbor, sit out at Aldo's and watch the boats, or a bit further you can go over to the Crows Nest restaurant and bar next to the harbor and at the beach.  A morning or evening walk to the wharf is always nice.  And did I mention the Boardwalk is close by? In fa
host_about: I am an RN and been with the VA for over 20 years. I enjoy my work very much.  Also I am a runner,  I started a running program end of March in 2013.  First a 10k, then half marathons, a marathon, and found myself at my first Boston Marathon in 2015.  I have 3 children.  My youngest is now a veteran!! My husband Roy  is retired from IT. I love traveling, meeting people and being a host of my family's beach place in Santa Cruz.

description: Om Oasis is a beautiful and lush retreat center on several acres of a remote and peaceful  15 acre mountain top property. We are 10-15 minutes up the mountain and partially off-grid with little to no cell reception but with a great WiFi connection. There are a total of 7 guest accommodations (including this one) spread out over our developed 3 acres, making it always a very private experience and easy to distance.

Raine and her family live part time in Hawai'i and part time at our beautiful Retreat in the Santa Cruz Mountains of California. Our onsite staff lives at our Retreat year round and are happy to provide outstanding healing and wellness services during your stay with us. 

Safe Travels & welcome OM.

description: Welcome to Beach Hill, one of the most sought out neighborhoods in Santa Cruz! name: Urban Homestead & Micro-Farm. Amazing Stay!
description:
Welcome to your own urban farm in Santa Cruz, California!

Our modest 2 bed, 2 bath home sits nestled on a peaceful, vibrant 1/2 acre organic urban farm perfectly located and close to everything – the beach, downtown Santa Cruz, 41st Avenue and Capitola village.

Escape the conventional and step outside your door and experience the tranquility of homestead life; gather eggs, harvest flowers, fruits, vegetables and berries.

Experience the dream!
neighborhood_overview:
The Live Oak neighborhood is an urban-rural neighborhood centrally located in Santa Cruz county with easy access to some of the finest surfing and beaches in Santa Cruz. You'll find everything you need just a short distance from your doorstep. Whole Foods and 41st Avenue with its popular shopping and dining are one mile away.

And when you're ready to explore downtown Santa Cruz, you'll find that it's just a short drive or bike ride away. From its eclectic shops and boutiques to its vibrant nightlife and cultural attractions, there's always something new and exciting to discover in Santa Cruz!

Whether you're looking for adventure, relaxation, or simply a change of pace, Live Oak is the perfect place to call home during your Santa Cruz vacation.

name: Country Retreat
description:
My home is located in the country. Looking out the living room window you will see our huge Redwood Tree. Beyond that you see Mountains and Farmlands. I am offering you the experience of staying in the country where you can have the feeling of being far away yet you are close to so many wonderful attractions: We are located approximately
one mile from the Watsonville Municipal Airport and The Beach is only 10 minutes away, Santa Cruz is 20 minutes away and Monterey/Carmel 30 minutes.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is spread out with neighbors 100's of yards away. Some vegetable farmers and some interesting Organic Farming close by.
When you visit  Country Retreat in Watsonville, you will find a relaxing and spacious home on three acres  away from the hustle bustle of life in the suburbs or the city…You will pass through farm land and travel on a private  road to your adventure in the country.  If you would like to explore the area you will have more choices than you have time for.  Besides our close proximity to Santa Cruz, Capitola, and the Monterey Peninsula, there is a lot to do and see right here in Watsonville . Some of my personal favorites are listed below.
I always suggest that visitors check out  Gizdich Ranch. They are local apple growers and have a bakery/pie shop at the farm..They make amazing Apple pies, Berry  pies, and of course Pumpkin pies. Buy a whole pie to take home or you can have a good sized slice..plain or ala mode..either outdoor on the pic
host_about:
My name is Dan O’Bannon and I have been a self employed Cabinet Maker for the past 33 years and  have been working with  my right hand Man, my Son Matt, for the past 10 years.   I enjoy nature and animals.  My Cat, Will Feral, was a wild stray that I took in,  he keeps me entertained.  I enjoy watching and attending Baseball games,  watching movies,  listening to music, and spending time with family and friends.  I have done some background acting (although not lately) in a few movies and TV shows  over the past 15 years and had a lot of fun playing a Barbosa Pirate in the first  "Pirates of the Caribbean" movie with my Son and Brother.  I've also enjoyed singing and playing the guitar with my Son Matt and my Brothers in the past.  
I moved to Santa Cruz in 1970 and have lived at my Country Home in Watsonville for the past 20 years.  Keeping up three acres, running my business and spending time with family & friends keeps me busy!   I have a very full life and I am grateful!

name: Thoughtfully decorated with amazing natural light!
description:
•1150 sq ft
•Upper Level: open floor plan LR/DR/Kitchen +2 BR/1B

•Rio Del Mar neighborhood in Aptos, CA


@aptos.cutest - follow us on Instagram!
neighborhood_overview:
The picturesque town of Aptos is in an unincorporated area of Santa Cruz County. It is a home to historic Aptos Village, and the gateway to the Forest of Nisene Marks State Park.

Redwoods and the sea in one idyllic setting!

Rio Del Mar means “River to the Sea” in Spanish, and was coined simply as a catchy-sounding name for a new subdivision in coastal Aptos. The name has no significance beyond that. The neighborhood is popular for a number of reasons, not least of which are a number of beaches close by.

The area is known for fog, although in truth the number of foggy days is not that great, and when there is fog, it often burns off by late morning or early afternoon, leading to warm and sunny days spring through fall. Winters are normally wet, with the heaviest rainfall occurring between October and March.

The house is located in a quiet family neighborhood. You can often spot deers in the back yard and wonder at birds from the deck.

neighborhood_overview:
Capitola is an intimate beach village tucked in a river valley in Santa Cruz County on the Monterey Bay. Located an hour away from San Jose and an hour and a half from San Francisco, Capitola enjoys a lively population full of tradition and an interesting history.
The City's wharf and riverside areas remind one of a village in France or perhaps a Mediterranean coast in Italy. Capitola Village is located along a wide beach with a breathtaking view of Monterey Bay and is home to numerous craft galleries, boutiques and restaurants. It is here where the Begonia Festival takes place each Labor Day weekend, featuring flower-draped floats and the must-see sand castle contest. Each fall the village also hosts the Annual Capitola Art & Wine Festival, which brings in over 170 artists, 10 wineries and numerous food vendors. Other visitor attractions include the Capitola Historical Museum, Capitola Wharf, and the Capitola Mall.

name: Monterey Bay Tuscan-Style Country Home w/ Hot Tub
description: So much more than a place to drop your bags, come relax in this warm and inviting  three bedroom, two 1/2 bath, Tuscan-style home located in a country setting conveniently located between Santa Cruz and Monterey. Unwind on the two-acre property that boasts fruit trees, an herb garden, grape vines, and large wrap-around decks. Enjoy the hot tub, fire pit and bocce ball court right on the property. Upon arrival, savor the local flavors with a complimentary bottle of wine.
neighborhood_overview:
The Tuscan Country Home sits in a quiet neighborhood on two acres overlooking an orchard, pasture, and eucalyptus grove.

The home is just 10 minutes away from some of the most pristine beaches of Central Coast California. The local Seascape Resort offers patio dining and cocktails with picturesque views of the sunset. There are exceptional breweries in area and plenty of grocery stories -- all within a 10-15 minute drive.
Head 15 minutes south to Moss Landing for kayaking and whale watching, boat tours of Elkhorn Slough or continue on to Monterey Bay and Carmel.

Head north 15 minutes to Capitola where you can shop, surf and eat like a local. Stop by the wharf to pick up fresh fish or enjoy a romantic glass of wine at the Shadowbrook.

There is an abundance of wonderful things to do and see in the area! With over 40 years living in Santa Cruz, Denise has a vast knowledge of the area and can make recommendations to suit your needs.
host_about:
As a decorative painter and antique collector, with an eye for interior design and a passion for hospitality, I have curated three entirely unique and beautiful stays that offer guests an unforgettable, restorative experience (swipe through to see them all).

My Italian heritage is at the heart of my approach to hospitality and design. From colour and texture to rustic design details, local wines and the pizza rolls that greet guests upon their arrival, the Italian influence is clear. 

When it comes to hosting, I pride myself on providing a warm and welcoming environment for each and every guest. With quality at the heart of my philosophy, I go above and beyond to ensure that all of my guests have a remarkable stay.

name: Redwood Retreat - 191203 - FOR SALE
description: CABIN FOR SALE, book soon… Enjoy Redwoods while relaxing on large deck or inside by indoor woodstove  (woodstove fee $50/2 night stay). Our rustic, remote cabin, surrounded by Redwoods, is perfect for water conserving, quiet guests who want to get away from it all to relax & unwind. Please be respectful to neighbors & follow house rules/no trespassing. Limited Cell & Satellite WIFI.  Seasonal, Self service wood burning heated cedar hot tub additional fee $200 & advance notice.
neighborhood_overview:
As as courtesy to our small, tightknit community, all neighbors are notified of guest count and arrival/departure dates. Neighbors properties have surveillance on their property and shared roads to alert them of trespassers. [Penal Code 602 PC - Trespassers will be prosecuted. The offense is a misdemeanor that carries a maximum sentence of 6 months in jail and a fine of $1000.00.]

Cabin is in the middle of a Redwood Forest surrounded by working cattle ranch with nearby and visible neighbors who take trespassing very seriously. Private road to our cabin it to only be used for accessing cabin via auto, IT IS NOT A WALKING TRAIL FOR AIRBNB GUESTS. It also can have neighbors' unfriendly dogs on it. Cows are not to be disturbed or approached.

Like any rural neighborhood, you will hear noises including dogs, roosters, chickens, ducks, chain saws, generators, blowers, tractors, trucks, distant shooting practice, visitors in travel trailers and RV's and tents etc.
host_about: My co host, Matt, and I look forward to hosting a quiet retreat for guests who can be respectful to our neighbors.  I greatly appreciate guests with strong communication and believe it is the key to making the whole Airbnb experience pleasant and smooth for everyone.  My dream is that guests will return over and over again and share the cabin with their family and friends and make memories over the years.

name: Coastal Hacienda in Aptos - 4 bedrooms & 3 baths
description: Ideally located 1.5 miles from both Rio Del Mar Beach and Nisene Marks Forest, with leafy views from every window, the open floor plan and outdoor spaces set our vacation home apart.  Easy access to Highway One provides easy access to other sites- Santa Cruz is about 10 minutes away, while Monterey and Carmel are about a 45 minute drive to the south.  We also enjoy the large fireplace, big screen TV and cozy sectional for at-home days.  And the  kitchen is  both well-equipped and cheery.
neighborhood_overview: The house is in a quiet, country like setting on a semi-private road.  But there is some noise from Highway One, below the house.  In renting it for over 20 years (on VRBO) we have had just two complaints.  But noise levels are subjective and happy guests are everything to us.  Please contact us for more details if that may be an issue for your group.
host_about: My husband Lannie and I own Aptos Oaks, a spacious "vintage" property with lots of history which we enjoy sharing with friends, family and selected others.  :)  The income from rentals goes right back into the property- we have a long list of desired improvements and renos!  We love travel (our photo is from Argentina) and have many places on our list.  We like to stay in small, family run hotels, B&B's and other unique properties.  We will truly care for your property as we do our own.  Our family motto is: Feed the People!  We love good food shared with good friends and connecting with others in a meaningful way.  After all, we are all in this together.

name: Whiskey Hollow A-Frame: As feat'd in Condé Nast!
description: Featured in Condé Nast's "30 Cozy A-Frame Cabins for Cold-Weather Getaways", Whiskey Hollow is a romantic retreat!  View majestic Redwoods from the loft bed, luxuriate in the oversized bathtub by candlelight, cozy up in front of the wood fireplace,  or cook a meal in the fully appointed kitchen.  Nestled in the woods, you would never guess that it's only 2 miles to downtown Felton, 1.5 miles to Henry Cowell State Park, 15 min to downtown Santa Cruz, and 20 min to the beach (Permit #191282).
neighborhood_overview:
If vacation means not cooking, downtown Felton offers multiple dining opportunities just five minutes away. A few of our favorites: Cowboy Bar & Grill, Sushi San, and Redwood Pizza . Scotts Valley is about 15 minutes away and offers all the amenities of a city (in case you're craving a fancy cupcake, See's candy or want to catch a movie on the big screen). Drive a few more minutes and you're in Santa Cruz at the beach, where you can find fresh crab, locally roasted coffee (Verve!), and a vegan bakery, as well as the renowned Bookshop Santa Cruz--a must if you are a book lover.

Nearby activities include hiking, surfing, zip-lining, mountain biking, and Roaring Camp Railroad. In the cabin you will find a binder filled with our dining recommendations (as well as addresses, phone numbers and hours for each restaurant), information on local activities ranging from Pescadero down to Carmel, and books about the area to help you plan your stay.
host_about: I grew up in a log cabin my dad built in a tiny town in the mountains of north Idaho. I have lived on both coasts of the US where I have worked as a marine research scientist, educator, & nonprofit leader. My family & community are my priorities, and - in my spare time - I love to be outside, woodworking, SCUBA diving, & am otherwise heavily involved in Breakthrough for Men, a men's group that helps participants be the best man they can be.

You can walk to all sorts of food and dining options, so you definitely won't go hungry! There is a large range of options from waterfront dining, to casual eateries, to quick bites (donuts, pizza slice, tacos, etc.).

While being to close to many coastal amenities, the house is located in a residential neighborhood. You are away from the hustle bustle of the side-by-side beach condos, and will have more space for larger groups and to spread out.

There are so many places all in walkable distance to explore, so make sure to do some basic planning. Definitely hit Capitola Beach, Pleasure Point, and the 41st Avenue restaurants and shops!

name: 3 BD Victorian Flat Steps to Beach and Boardwalk
description: Welcome to Beach Hill, one of the most sought out neighborhoods in Santa Cruz. My cozy family friendly updated & remodeled 1868 Painted Lady purple Victorian home is only a TWO MINUTE WALK TO THE BEACH & BOARDWALK, many restaurants, bars, & cafes! Walk to downtown in ten minutes. View the beautiful Pacific ocean as you step outside, and enjoy the soothing ocean breeze. The perfect destination for an escape to paradise.
neighborhood_overview: You can't find a better getaway in Santa Cruz. Come stay in a beautiful classic Victorian home that is close to 150 years old right by the beach and boardwalk. Get away from the hustle and bustle as you're on the very top of the hill, but all you need to do is walk two minutes and you're in the center of it all. Downtown is very close by, perfect if you want to park your car and explore Santa Cruz by walking around. Beach Hill is a fantastic neighborhood and is one of the most historic areas in Santa Cruz.
host_about:
Hello, I am Rex Solway! I have lived in Santa Cruz my entire life and know the town like the back of my hand. I enjoy traveling, fine dining, photography, and the ocean -- I wouldn't be able to live far from the beach! I would like to call myself an avid sushi lover, adore cats (but no worries if you have allergies, no kitties live here!), and often find myself critiquing the films and shows I watch with friends and family. I worship the sun, but thrive under the moon and the stars when it's dark outside. I’m always looking for the next adventure that awaits around the corner. 

I am personally dedicated to providing the best possible experience for you and your family, and will do my best to create a unique experience you'll never forget!

name: Little Cabin
description: Relax among redwoods and listen to the creek rushing below in this backyard boho, cabin retreat. This private studio is perched creekside under the redwoods and an easy walk to markets, shops and restaurants in downtown Boulder Creek. We are in the Santa Cruz Mountains and 35 mins from the SJC Airport and 20 mins from Santa Cruz. It's a great central location to explore many nearby redwood forest, coastal parks or take a day trip along the iconic Hwy 1 to Monterey, Big Sur or San Francisco.
neighborhood_overview:
Little Cabin is within easy walking distance to several local markets, shops and restaurants. Historic Boulder Creek has a rugged and independent spirit and is the gateway to Big Basin, California's oldest state park where you can walk among ancient redwood trees. Outdoor and nature enthusiasts will enjoy the close vicinity to numerous state and county parks and beaches. Santa Cruz and the Pacific Coast Highway 1 are only 20 minutes away. We are located in the heart of the Santa Cruz Mountains in the San Lorenzo Valley and a 35 minute drive from the San Jose International Airport.

name: Redwood Hilltop Retreat
description: This mountain family home is perfect with breathtaking views of the Santa Cruz Mountains. The large wrapping deck provides the perfect space for indoor-outdoor living, while the indoors offers a cozy feel with a wood burning fireplace and all the essentials of a well loved home. Located in a redwood forest with 260 degree sweeping views. 10 mins to Santa Cruz beaches, 40 min to Monterey, 5 min to Mt Hermon Center and concerts at Felton Music Hall. Excellent location for sightseeing & activities.
neighborhood_overview: Mt. Hermon is a small community near Felton,  just a 10-minute drive to Santa Cruz and beaches. The area is full of inviting trails to explore, wonderful redwood forests with beautiful creeks and idyllic scenery. We’re a few minutes from the Mount Hermon Christian Conference Center which offers a world class Zip Line course through the redwood canopy. The Mt. Hermon coffee shop, book store, and soda fountain are open for guests (check their schedule for days/times). Roaring Camp’s steam train ride through the redwoods and to the beach is 5 mins away, perfect for families and guests. Henry Cowell Redwood Park offers incredible forest views and a self-guided tour of ancient redwoods. Safeway grocery store, Wild Roots Organic Grocery store, Pete's , White Raven and Mountain Roasting Coffee shops, CVS drug store, and restaurants less than a mile away.
host_about: We’ve enjoyed Santa Cruz, Felton, Mt Hermon and its surrounding areas for generations. Our family would love to welcome you to stay at our wonderful home that’s blessed us for many years. I love the outdoors and enjoy the beach, fishing, hiking, bike riding and nature photography to name a few! We have a wonderful community here in the mountains and coast, come and visit to be renewed, refreshed & explore the many things to do and see from mountains to the sea!

Nearby you will find several places to grab a bite including the Crow's Nest and Cafe El Palomar on the beach, Johnny's Harborside at the nearby boat harbor, the Harbor Cafe and L&L Hawaiian BBQ, to name a few. There are various museums in the area including The Santa Cruz Museum of Art and History downtown, the Seymour Marine Discovery Center, and the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary Exploration Center. 1 bd/1ba, fenced yard, heated bathroom floor, and toilet seat. Glass fireplace in the living room and bedroom, skylight over the bed with blackout shade.

Car charging station is located at Nob Hill Shopping center with about 15 charging units. Only about 5 minutes from Ryder Rancheria, we ask that you not charge vehicles at our property.

Hiking; Henry Cowell state park, Loch Lomand (March to Oct), Fall Creek, Big Bison state park

name: WOW! Luxury 5000sf Oceanview next to Main Beach
description: Ultimate vacation destination for your gathering- Luxurious home across from beach & wharf in the heart of Santa Cruz fun! You'll enjoy over 5,000 square feet of luxurious accommodations- 9 private rooms (most w/ adjoining baths) beds for 20 guests, including 2 full chef's kitchens w Viking appliances &stunning views, and a full outdoor kitchen w/ an enormous patio w/views of the entire Monterey Bay.  Multiple master suites w/ 4 king beds, 3 queens & 4 bunks (8 twin beds). Come relax and enjoy.
neighborhood_overview:
Your group can walk to just about everything, or just sit back and enjoy in this spectacular retreat. Located directly across the street from the beautiful Santa Cruz Wharf, famous Cowells Beach, and the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary Visitor's Center. Walk to the world famous Santa Cruz Boardwalk, where you can enjoy mini-golf, rollercoasters, bowling, an arcade and more. Take the summertime trolley offering service to downtown Santa Cruz with a stop outside your front door. Walk to the lighthouse museum at Lighthouse Field or hop on the old fashion locomotive train to Roaring Camp Redwoods. Enjoy 30+ restaurants and shops, rent surfboards, watch the whales and dolphins. Plan some time to drop in the exclusive Jack O'Neil Lounge and listen to some live jazz.

Note: City has strict restrictions against parties, so no large parties/events are allowed. Santa Cruz City Vacation Rental Permit#'s: STR18-108 & STR18-109

name: Rustic Modern 1 BR  in Sunny Seabright
description:
Our Seabright Beach place has been in the family for over 50 years. A recent remodel brings the space up to date with our goal to make it especially comfortable and light, a retreat where you will be able to relax after a day of adventure, riding the Big Dipper, wine/beer tasting or beach fun.
Sleep in a comfy king size bed in a room with room darkening window coverings. The sofa has a pull out queen size bed. Also, we have a fold out bed in the bedroom closet.
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is nicely situated where you can easily walk down to the Boardwalk (no need to drive!), yet  we are just across the river (walk the famous train trestle) so not in the hustle and bustle of the Boardwalk area.  Also walk to beautiful Seabright Beach,  enjoy a wide variety of  delicious restaurants nearby , including the Brewery, Enfer Pizza, Tramonte, Bettys Burgers, and more.  There is coffee, tea, smoothies, bagels at Java Junction or find nearby Verve coffee Roastery where they roast the coffee on site.  Take a stroll down to the Harbor, enjoy calamari at Aldo's, a fresh fish meal at Johnny's Harbor Cafe, or sit out at the Crows Nest for beautiful ocean views.  The nearby Ocean View park has great slides for your kids.  This park is also known to our kids as the "wax paper" park.  They would take wax paper on the slides to go faster!   I love that we can hear the roar of the Big Dipper, excitement from the riders, the barking of the sea lions, and at high tide, the c

First a 10k, then half marathons, a marathon, and found myself at my first Boston Marathon in 2015.  I have 3 children.  My youngest is now a veteran!! My husband Roy  is retired from IT. neighborhood_overview:
Central location! 8 minute stroll to boardwalk. Relaxing 15 minute walk to SeaBright Beach. Walk to downtown with all its cafes, shops and restaurants! Only 8 minutes!

Santa Cruz is often valued for its location; tucked between the north and central coast of California, Santa Cruz has a mild climate, miles of sandy beaches, and a coastal redwood system that is hauntingly beautiful. But Santa Cruz offers family vacationers much more than just an ideal location, Santa Cruz is a family vacation paradise! From old fashioned carnival games to surf lessons, a Santa Cruz family vacation combines a love for modern amusements with the best of the outdoors. In Santa Cruz there is never a choice between the city and the rural life: both are essential parts of a Santa Cruz family vacation. Every member of the family will love a Santa Cruz family vacation; your family will tell stories and remember anecdotes of your family vacation for years. You’ll find that smiles and laughter come

name: Escape to "Enseñada Del Sol" Beach House
description: Our lovely beach home, Enseñada Del Sol, is just over a block from Sunny Cove beach. It is the perfect space to enjoy a relaxing and private Santa Cruz experience.  Our spacious custom built home was lovingly designed and decorated in a beautiful and unique Talavera style.  High end finishes and thoughtful touches abound at Enseñada Del Sol. Our home is a delightful sanctuary that is a clean, well-appointed and safe place for family and friends to gather and enjoy all that Santa Cruz offers.
neighborhood_overview:
Enseñada Del Sol is in a fantastic and very central location. The beautiful tide pools at Corcoran beach are just down the street, and a very short walk (less than two blocks) will take you to Sunny Cove or Santa Maria (or "Mo's", as locals know it), both great family beaches! Mo's is a great beach to take a quiet and invigorating long walk.

There is a Starbucks around the corner and there are a number of tasty restaurants within walking distance; and don't miss out on the fun local brewery. On Sundays, there is a charming little Farmer's Market only a short walk away.

The Boardwalk, the Wharf, Capitola Village and historic downtown Santa Cruz are all just a quick 10 minute drive. The Yacht Harbor and Twin Lakes Beach (with the Crow's Nest, Cafe el Palomar and Java Junction) are a three minute drive or a nice 15 minute walk away. The area is extremely bike and walking friendly, so why not enjoy the area without dealing with the stresses of traffic!!!
host_about:
I live in Santa Cruz, California with my wonderful wife Katharina and our son Oliver. I am a professional Airbnb host and a former elementary school teacher and Katharina is an amazing person and an incredibly talented creative director. Oliver is a bright, energetic and friendly young man that loves the water, bike riding, history, exploring and solving the mysteries of the universe. We have one incredibly friendly and mellow cat (Dexter), six chickens and we enjoy spending time with friends--hiking, biking, great home-cooked meals, good wine and beer, and generally enjoying all that life has to offer.

We have a passion for travel--nothing is more exciting then finding yourself in a new and unfamiliar place with nothing to do but explore and interact with new people!

We are also extremely responsible people. We own our home and take great pride in having a place that is clean, comfortable and inviting. As guests in other people's homes, we feel the same responsibility and respect for their space.

name: Lower Westside Sanctuary by Natural Bridges  Beach
description:
From our family of beach bums to yours: welcome to our newly remodeled, coastal sanctuary on the quiet lower Westside of Santa Cruz. Stroll 5 minutes to Natural Bridges Beach by day. By night, stargaze from the hot tub or gather around the gas fire pit.

Wildlife abounds: from our resident hummingbirds and butterflies at home to occasional seal, otter and whale sightings at Natural Bridges. Hungry/thirsty? Stroll 10 minutes to the heart of Santa Cruz’s beer, wine, and foodie scene!
neighborhood_overview:
The lower Westside of Santa Cruz is a quiet, family-friendly haven that's still close to all the action. It's just a 5-minute walk to Natural Bridges Beach and State Park, which is known for its wildlife, including shore birds, migratory whales, seals and otters. Not to mention the Monarch Butterfly Sanctuary at the Park—visit in late October and into November to observe peak monarch migration.

For a bit more activity, you're also just a 10-minute drive to the Beach Boardwalk and within walking distance of Santa Cruz's thriving and creative brewery and winery district. The Seymour Marine Discovery Center—a community-supported marine science education center affiliated with UC-Santa Cruz—is also nearby.

neighborhood_overview:
Aptos is a coastal gem nestled in Santa Cruz County. With its stunning beaches, including Rio del Mar and Seacliff State Beach, it's a haven for sun-seekers and surf enthusiasts. This charming town boasts a laid-back vibe, a mix of boutique shops, and a vibrant dining scene, making it a perfect destination for a relaxing vacation. The iconic Cement Ship at Seacliff Beach is a must-see, and nearby forested parks like Nisene Marks offer hiking and biking trails. Aptos combines natural beauty, small-town charm, and easy access to the Santa Cruz Boardwalk, creating an ideal coastal escape for visitors.

This is a very quiet, family neighborhood. It is not a good place for gatherings or parties so please keep that in mind when booking this home. We are very respectful of our neighbors and will not tolerate loud noise past curfew and additional guests at the property.
host_about: O'Neal Vacation Rentals is a small team that is laser focused on hosting guests at amazing vacation rentals! We believe that memorable vacations are centered around beautiful homes that are comfortable and stocked with all the amenities that make for an amazing stay.

name: Beach Cottage near Sunny Cove and Santa Mo's
description:
Our lovely, bright & welcoming 2-bedroom (plus), 1-bath beach cottage is a close walk to Santa Maria Beach (Santa Mo’s) & Sunny Cove Beach. It has four comfortable beds & is spacious enough for up to six people, but is especially set up for couples & small families.

Want a longer stay than listed availability? Send me a note (we make the property available for five+ weeks at a time) & I can open up blocked days in between.

neighborhood_overview:
The Beach Cottage Near Sunny Cove and Santa Mo's is in a fantastic and central location. The beautiful tide pools at Corcoran beach are steps away and a very short walk (less than two blocks) will take you to Sunny Cove or Santa Maria (or "Mo's", as locals know it), both great family beaches! Mo's is a great beach to take a quiet and invigorating long walk.

There is a Starbucks around the corner and there are a number of tasty restaurants within walking distance; and don't miss out on the fun local brewery nearby! On Sundays there is a charming little Farmer's Market, also a short walk away.

The Boardwalk, the Wharf, Capitola Village and historic downtown Santa Cruz are all just a quick 10 minute drive (or less then 20 minute bike ride). The Yacht Harbor and Twin Lakes Beach (with the Crow's Nest, Cafe el Palomar and Java Junction) are a three minute drive or a nice 15 minute walk away. The area is extremely bike and walking friendly, so why not enjoy the area w
host_about:
I live in Santa Cruz, California with my wonderful wife Katharina and our son Oliver. I am a professional Airbnb host and a former elementary school teacher and Katharina is an amazing person and an incredibly talented creative director. Oliver is a bright, energetic and friendly young man that loves the water, bike riding, history, exploring and solving the mysteries of the universe. We have one incredibly friendly and mellow cat (Dexter), six chickens and we enjoy spending time with friends--hiking, biking, great home-cooked meals, good wine and beer, and generally enjoying all that life has to offer.

We have a passion for travel--nothing is more exciting then finding yourself in a new and unfamiliar place with nothing to do but explore and interact with new people!

We are also extremely responsible people. We own our home and take great pride in having a place that is clean, comfortable and inviting. As guests in other people's homes, we feel the same responsibility and respect for their space.

name: The Nests at Camp Cruz. A Redwood Glamping Retreat
description: Located a short drive from the bay area, Camp Cruz is a year-round glamping retreat in the redwoods ideal for people who want a camping experience without giving up basic living comforts. It is a perfect destination to unwind and create special memories in a secluded nature setting. It offers guests 1 or 2 private bedrooms: the Raven’s Nest (aircrete dome) and the Owl’s Nest (yurt). More guests are welcome if you bring your own tents. There is a full kitchen, a propane fire pit, showers, & more.
neighborhood_overview:
Our listing is located on just over 4 acres in a redwood forest up a canyon. Our location has a park-like setting. Our guests will have private use of the camp area, which is situated in a separate location on the property, but it is in close proximity to our home residence. Our closest neighbor is a Buddhist Retreat Center, which for the most part, is a quiet sanctuary. However, they do occasionally host weddings and if you are visiting on one of those weekends, you can expect to hear some noise/music from the reception, which always ends promptly at 10pm. Guests can also expect to hear some occasional road noise.
Because we are located in a wilderness area, we co-exist with wild life critters. They are around, but not often seen. The wild animals that live in our area include owls, hawks and other birds, foxes, coyotes, raccoons, skunks, squirrels, deer, bobcats and mountain lions.
host_about: We are a family of four. Ismael is a teacher who runs a local nonprofit outdoor education program for underserved youth (Growing Up Wild). Molly is a registered nurse. We have two fun loving boys. Our home, where the glamping retreat is located, is a private campground in the redwood forest. It is a beautiful and serene forest setting with a running creek and lots of wildlife.

name: Sunny Santa Cruz Bungalow
description:
Our bright and comfy bungalow is located in a unique neighborhood (tucked between a school and a tire shop—with a cool founder’s cemetery nearby) only a short walk to the Santa Cruz harbor and Twin Lakes beach. The open floor plan and large covered porch are an ideal place to relax and enjoy the beautifully landscaped yard and chickens––you'll love it!

Want to stay longer? Just send me a note, as we make the property available for five+ weeks at a time and can open up blocked days in between.
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a unique mix of residential, industrial and somewhat unusual. Our house is tucked between a small school and a tire shop (that is open M-F during normal house and Saturdays until noon). We’ve lived here ten years and the tire shop is a great neighbor. There is also a really cool Santa Cruz founder’s cemetery a block away—it’s a great place to walk around and explore the history of the areas early settlers.
host_about:
I live in Santa Cruz, California with my wonderful wife Katharina and our son Oliver. I am a professional Airbnb host and a former elementary school teacher and Katharina is an amazing person and an incredibly talented creative director. Oliver is a bright, energetic and friendly young man that loves the water, bike riding, history, exploring and solving the mysteries of the universe. We have one incredibly friendly and mellow cat (Dexter), six chickens and we enjoy spending time with friends--hiking, biking, great home-cooked meals, good wine and beer, and generally enjoying all that life has to offer.

We have a passion for travel--nothing is more exciting then finding yourself in a new and unfamiliar place with nothing to do but explore and interact with new people!

We are also extremely responsible people. We own our home and take great pride in having a place that is clean, comfortable and inviting. As guests in other people's homes, we feel the same responsibility and respect for their space.

name: Santa Cruz Redwoods
description:
Come enjoy a getaway where you can experience the redwoods, the beach, The Boardwalk, and much more!

Make yourself at home in our spacious (895 sq. ft, deck excluded) and newly remodeled guest suite (studio plus bedroom). There is a kitchenette with a microwave and mini-fridge, and a dining room table to enjoy snacks, light meals, or takeout/delivery.

The deck looks out to the redwoods, where you can enjoy a morning coffee or a glass of wine al fresco.
neighborhood_overview:
The guest suite is special because of its remote feel of the woods, despite its close proximity to Santa Cruz's beautiful beaches. It is located at the end of a cul-de-sac in a residential neighborhood. Main Beach and The Boardwalk are 3.3 miles away, with tasty restaurants and cute shops even closer on Pacific Avenue.

Strolling Pacific Avenue; going to one of Santa Cruz's many beaches to sun, surf, boogie board, or stroll; cycling; playing arcade or carnival games or hopping on rides at The Boardwalk; hiking the Redwoods; going wine tasting; there's something for everyone! See our favorite spots listed in our on-site information packet.

name: Monterey Bay Tuscan-Style  Art Studio
description: Relax in this warm and inviting  Art Studio located in a country setting, conveniently located between Santa Cruz and Monterey. Unwind on the 2 acre property that boasts fruit trees,  herb garden, grape vines, and a large deck. Find all of the peace you would imagine of the Italian countryside in this charming, one of a kind artist’s studio complete with a kitchenette, queen bed, and private bathroom and shower. Upon arrival, savor the local flavors with a complimentary bottle of wine.
neighborhood_overview:
The Tuscan Country Art Studio is just 10 minutes away from some of the most pristine beaches of Central Coast California.

The local Seascape Resort offers patio dining and cocktails with picturesque views of the sunset. There are exceptional breweries in area and plenty of grocery stories -- all within a 10-15 minute drive.

Head 15 minutes south to Moss Landing for kayaking and whale watching, or boat tours of Elkhorn Slough, or continue on to Monterey Bay and Carmel.

Head north 15 minutes to Capitola where you can shop, surf and eat like a local. Stop by the wharf to pick up fresh fish or enjoy a romantic glass of wine at the Shadowbrook.

There is an abundance of wonderful things to do and see in the area! With over 40 years living in Santa Cruz, Denise has a vast knowledge of the area and can make recommendations to suit your needs.
host_about:
As a decorative painter and antique collector, with an eye for interior design and a passion for hospitality, I have curated three entirely unique and beautiful stays that offer guests an unforgettable, restorative experience (swipe through to see them all).

My Italian heritage is at the heart of my approach to hospitality and design. From colour and texture to rustic design details, local wines and the pizza rolls that greet guests upon their arrival, the Italian influence is clear. 

When it comes to hosting, I pride myself on providing a warm and welcoming environment for each and every guest. With quality at the heart of my philosophy, I go above and beyond to ensure that all of my guests have a remarkable stay.

name: ❤ of Capitola Village with Private Yard + Parking
description: Welcome to Surf Loft! This one bedroom, one bath mid-century inspired loft apartment is located in desirable Capitola Village and just steps away from the beach. neighborhood_overview:
Capitola Village is one of the most charming beach towns on the coast of California and home to some of the most trendy shops, restaurants, wine bars and tap houses!

Must dos during your visit:
~Delight in a slice of pizza at Pizza My Heart at one of the benches along the oceanfront.
~Indulge in a bacon and prawn Bloody Mary at The Sand Bar on their back patio.
~Take in the views from over the Stockton Avenue Bridge.
~Admire the views of the historical colorful Venetian Court along the beachfront.
~Stroll to the very end of the pier for a rooftop panoramic view of Capitola from The Wharf House.
~For a legendary experience head up the hill to Shadowbrook Restaurant in the evening and enjoy live music in the Rockroom (Typically Thurs., Fri. & Sat.). There is no place like it!
~Head to the upper village to Gayle's Bakery & Rosticceria for Capitola's grab-and-go landmark. Be sure to pull a ticket number!

name: Monterey Bay Ultimate Glamping in New Airstream
description: Enjoy the ultimate glamping experience with the convenience and comfort of home! The plush, 25ft. International Airstream (2021) is nestled in an orchard brimming with organic fruit in the heart of the Central Coast. So much more than a place to drop your bags, come relax in this warm and inviting, new, Airstream located in a country setting, conveniently located between Santa Cruz and Monterey. This is an ideal spot for those looking for a romantic escape or a bit of sun and adventure.
neighborhood_overview:
The Tuscan Tin Can is just 10 minutes away from some of the most pristine beaches of Central Coast California.

The local Seascape Resort offers patio dining and cocktails with picturesque views of the sunset. There are exceptional breweries in area and plenty of grocery stories -- all within a 10-15 minute drive.
Head 15 minutes south to Moss Landing for kayaking and whale watching, boat tours of Elkhorn Slough or continue on to Monterey Bay and Carmel.

Head north 15 minutes to Capitola where you can shop, surf and eat like a local. Stop by the wharf to pick up fresh fish or enjoy a romantic glass of wine at the Shadowbrook.

There is an abundance of wonderful things to do and see in the area! With over 40 years living in Santa Cruz, Denise has a vast knowledge of the area and can make recommendations to suit your needs.
host_about:
As a decorative painter and antique collector, with an eye for interior design and a passion for hospitality, I have curated three entirely unique and beautiful stays that offer guests an unforgettable, restorative experience (swipe through to see them all).

My Italian heritage is at the heart of my approach to hospitality and design. From colour and texture to rustic design details, local wines and the pizza rolls that greet guests upon their arrival, the Italian influence is clear. 

When it comes to hosting, I pride myself on providing a warm and welcoming environment for each and every guest. With quality at the heart of my philosophy, I go above and beyond to ensure that all of my guests have a remarkable stay.
