name: Beach Hill Hideaway - Steps to Boardwalk/Beach
description:
Inviting beach house just 1.5 blocks from the Boardwalk, beach, wharf, restaurants and walking distance to downtown and the best surf spots.

Full kitchen, dining & living area, office, deck with dining/patio seating and BBQ. Master suite with king bed & en suite bath. The 2nd & 3rd bedrooms feature queen beds with a shared full bath. Cozy family room has a big screen TV, games and the office has queen pull out sofa. Outdoor shower for cleaning off sand when you return from the beach.
neighborhood_overview: We are located 1.5 blocks from the famed Santa Cruz Boardwalk, beach, wharf and some of the best surfing in the world on West Cliff drive. So much to see and do just steps away.
host_about:
Hi there! 

I'm Dominique.  I have always loved living near the water and spent much of my childhood living on a houseboat in Key West, Florida. (Pretty sure I have seawater running through my veins.) I have lived in several places before making Santa Cruz my permanent home, including; Mexico, NYC, New Orleans (I tend to only live in places Jimmy Buffet sings about. ; ) ) 

My day job for the past 25 years has been teaching and owning a Pilates studio and my husband Erik is an "almost" retired (can't get him to actually leave) Fireman/Paramedic. 

We love to travel and have stayed in Airbnbs all over the world. We get what makes a "home away from home" great and how much the place you stay can impact your experience of a location. 

We are excited to share our Santa Cruz home with you. We raised our daughter here for the first 10 years of her life so far... enjoying the beach, Boardwalk, wharf and walks along West Cliff.  We have spent so many happy memories here and we're convinced you and your family and friends will too!

neighborhood_overview:
Located in a quaint, safe and quiet residential neighborhood. A short walk to the beach or town. Close to Seacliff restaurants and shops (Manuel's Mexican, Pizza One, Mary Anne’s Ice Cream, Ambrosia Indian food).
Burger in Aptos is a bar/restaurant close by that offers casual dining as well. Safeway grocery store, Aptos natural foods, and AJ’s natural food store both within 1-2 miles.
A short walk from the house on Seacliff (0.2 miles away) will give you an incredible view of the Monterey Bay. A 2-3 mile drive to Capitola village and Rio Del Mar.
Short walk to Nisene State Park. Get in through Aptos Rancho trail (1.1miles).
Only 8-10 miles from the westside of Santa Cruz, downtown Santa Cruz and UCSC. Only about 6 miles to the harbor. Take a sailboat cruise from the harbor on the Chardonnay or O’Neil Charter. Take a surf lesson at Cowells. See the elephant seals at Año Nuevo. Kayak or bird/whale watch and eat great sea food at Moss Landing just 14 miles south. E

name: Coastal Redwoods Retreat
description: Our home has gorgeous views of our famous redwood trees from every window. We even have two trees coming thru our deck that’s so peaceful to enjoy day or night. Only 15 min up the road , a beautiful ride thru the redwoods you can be at the fun beaches of Santa Cruz. It’s a great couples get away,a few friends or a small family vacation at this peaceful, beautiful setting in the redwoods.
neighborhood_overview: Felton is a great little town and your stay at 1156 lakeside dr is in a perfect location for your visit. I’ll give you a idea of what’s near.  One mile to Henry Cowells State Park. This is a absolutely wonderful park, great hiking trails and a nice creek to cool off in. Downtown Felton ,population 4800 has Felton Music Hall. Great live music and serves food. Roaring camp you can take a train ride thru the redwoods or take it to the beach boardwalk where the rides are. Abbott’s Thrift store is well known for some great deals and tues 1-4 the Felton Farmers Market is happening downtown. Make sure you read the binders in our home with dinning places that are good in Felton too. Our famous Mystery Spot you have to see too. You may see turkeys and deer on the road driving to the house so be careful.
host_about: My husband Al and I Debbie love this home because of the beauty it offers with huge redwoods surrounding us.  We both are in our retirement years and what better way to enjoy it but be in a peaceful setting as what this home had to offer plus we can get to the beaches of Santa Cruz in 20 min, which we also love. The best  of two worlds. Me being  a retired flight attendant and my husband a retired bartender/service industry job know what good hospitality is. We love sharing the beauty of our home and when it’s rented we will be gone but not far away. We have a place in Santa Cruz we will be staying at if you have a problem and need us. Our home is a two bedroom , one with a standard room and  second room is smaller with a small full size fouton in it but we also have a cottage that has full bath,mini Frig,micro,coffee maker and queen size fouton. Perfect for two couples or a family with older kids.

name: Coastal Architectural Gem in Capitola
description:
Nantucket-inspired cottage in Capitola designed by award-winning architect Tobin Dougherty. This iconic beach house has been showcased in many publications, including Sunset Magazine, Fine Homebuilding, and Better Homes and Gardens. It is a true architectural gem that I am honored to share with you and your loved ones.

neighborhood_overview:
Capitola is a quiet beach city about five miles from Santa Cruz, popular with weekenders from the San Francisco Bay Area and the Central Valley. This quaint seaside village began as a humble camp. Camp Capitola, as it was known, welcomed its first guests in 1874, making it the first beach resort in California.

Capitola hosts many fun events year-round, including live music, car shows, the Art and Wine festival, and more! The Capitola Twilight Concerts are hosted on Wednesday evenings during the summer months. All concerts begin at 6 p.m. and take place at the Esplanade.

With over 75 years of history, Shadowbrook is one of the most unique restaurants in the West.

name: Seabright Retreat: Walk to the Beach & Boardwalk
description:
A lovely duplex situated at the end of a cul-de-sac in the sunny Seabright neighborhood, its easy to forget you’re in a city, when you can hear the waves and sea-lions barking from the front patio. At night you'll be surrounded by a star-studded sky, in a super quiet and safe location.

Built in 1928 and fully modernized, this retreat is a stylish and fun light filled space. Walk to the beach (0.7 mi), Harbor (0.5) Boardwalk (1.1), downtown (1.5) , Rio Theater (0.5), UCSC (3) and so much more.
neighborhood_overview:
Seabright is one of the most desirable locations in Santa Cruz. Known locally for its ample sunshine, the fog usually burns off here before other parts of the city, cute houses and friendly neighbors.

Just a 10 minute walk to the harbor (w/ access to Arana Gulch nature space), 12 to the beach, 20 to the boardwalk or a very quick drive to all of them. It's easy to get to University of California Santa Cruz (UCSC), downtown, and all other Santa Cruz locations.

An Epicureans delight surrounded by the best Italian restaurants in town: La Posta, Tramonti, Lillians Kitchen and Sugo Pasta Bar. Not to mention Sante Adairius Brewery with Michelin-star chef Bookies Pizzas, Engfers wood-fired pizzas and Linda's Sea-breeze Cafe

It's the perfect place to make your home base while exploring the city of Santa Cruz and the beautiful nature that surrounds us.

name: Katie's place  between Santa Cruz and Monterey
description:

neighborhood_overview: Katie’s place is located in a safe, quiet, family-orientated neighbourhood, next to Watsonville Slough Wildlife Preserve and trails, which attracts numerous bird species. Pajaro Dunes (less than 4 miles away) and Sunset beaches are local favourites and uncrowded, where you can walk for miles and enjoy peace and tranquility. Located just south of Santa Cruz off Highway 1, Seascape Beach Resort gorgeous accommodations overlooking the Monterey Bay.
The entire resort sits atop breathtaking bluffs overlooking the ocean and beaches below. The walking path in the center of the resort leads down to the beach.
On the resort you will find The Seascape Park, Numerous walking paths, The Sanderlings Restaurant and bar, 3 pools and spas, and a full gym (gym access with additional fee paid on-site).
Across the street from the resort you will find Seascape Village which offers restaurants, cafes and shops.
The PGA rated Seascape Golf Course is only 5 minutes from the resort.
In the Heart of Aptos just over three miles or 10 minutes drive away you will discover what happens when the redwoods meet the sea. name: Loft Apartment in the Mountains!
description: This is a new loft apartment with a separate entrance on the far side of our garage.  We have 3 units in our compound arranged around a central garden, all of which sit in our 10 acres of park like property surrounded by redwoods, pines and firs.  We have our own gardens, fruit orchards, meadows and our own private pond which you can walk around.  Next door is a well known winery and tasting room, and only 3 miles down the hill are the beautiful coastal beaches.
neighborhood_overview:
We are in the mountains surrounded by redwoods, meadows and a winery. 1 mile up the road is an ecological preserve with great hiking. It is 3 miles down the mountain to a nice beach. The roads around us don't have a lot of cars so the area is great for bicycling. Go north on Highway One and you are at Davenport, an old whaling town with a nice restaurant and another nice beach. Just further north on the coast is Ano Nuevo State Park, where the giant elephant seals raise their babies on the beach each spring. Also close by are Big Basin State Park (unfortunately shut down temporarily after the fires), Wilder Ranch State Park, Henry Cowell State Park and many other great parks.

And of course, we are only 13 miles north of the wonderful town of Santa Cruz.

The apartment sits in the middle of a compound that includes a large garden, fruit orchard and 2 other guest units, protected by a deer fence. You can access our own pond which thru a pathway down the hill
host_about:
My day job is investing in technology, hosting startup events and I do some consulting.  But my wife and I also have this magical place in the Santa Cruz mountains, in a clearing amongst the redwoods, next to a great winery, and only 3 miles from the beach.   We have our own pond, and we have surrounded ourselves with fruit trees and floral gardens, which we hope you will enjoy.  When we are not around, our caretaker, Ed Olson, takes care of our guests.  

We hope to create a Shangri-la feel for our guests - totally relaxed in the mountains and nature, but with all the comforts of home.  We are also frequent travelers, so we know how important it is to feel at home when staying in new accomodations.

name: Beach Bunk-Bed Bungalow
description: This charming and cozy one bedroom bungalow is located in the heart of Santa Cruz's wonderful Seabright community, just steps to Seabright Beach. Walking distance to a variety of eateries, Santa Cruz Nature Museum, Beach Boardwalk, and Yacht Harbor, this is the perfect location for a trip to the beach or to lounge and listen to the waves in the back patio.
neighborhood_overview:
Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.

This is not a good place for gatherings or parties so please keep that in mind when booking this home. We are very respectful of our neighbors and will not tolerate loud noise past curfew and additional guests at the property.

name: Beach Town Country Stay - 10 min drive to beach
description: Hidden in the valley and vines, this cute and spacious 1 bedroom/1 bath unit privately located on our property is perfectly placed amongst the rolling hills and oak trees in Santa Cruz County. With an open concept living room and kitchen, this newly updated space has a walk-in shower, laundry room, and up-to-date appliances.If you are looking to rest your head after a long day of exploring Santa Cruz and the surrounding areas, our relaxing and tranquil homestead is your home away from home.
neighborhood_overview: The lovely home is set in the quiet countryside but is conveniently located just a 10 minute drive from the gorgeous Seacliff State Beach, 5 minute drive from the beautiful Corralitos Wine Trail, 15 minutes from the redwoods at Nisene Marks, 50 minutes from Monterey (the home of the Monterey Bay Aquarium), and 1 hour and 30 minutes from San Francisco. host_about:
My name is Jessica I am a single mom of an amazing 5 year old little boy. Yeah I tend to lead my intro about my son because he is a big part of who I am and well because he is awesome…haha! And because he makes me a better person, I wouldn’t be who I am without him. 
Anyway- I’m Jessica, I from Santa Cruz California. I work in the medical industry and love the outdoors, meeting new people, and trying new things. Some of my favorite places to travel are; Germany, Italy, Hawaii and Canada as well the US States.  My partner in crime (not real crime obviously) if my son is not with me is my other half Stephen (an Environmental Geologist). We love to travel as a couple and as a family. We are all very clean and I am a firm believer in treating others and their things the way you want to be treated, that’s what I like to model and teach my son. 
In short we are a fun loving, hardworking group that want to travel and teach my son the amazing learning experiences traveling has to offer.

name: Charming Santa Cruz Bungalow near Beach & Redwoods
description:
One-month minimum stay. Charming getaway in the perfect location...Downtown SC - 1 mile, Beach Boardwalk - 2 mi, Redwood hikes - 1 mi, Golf course - 1 mi, UC Santa Cruz - 3 mi, Pleasure Point (famous surf spot) 2.4 mi, Monterey - 30 mi, gorgeous wineries, beach/surf shops, Antiquing, Galleries, etc.

An authentic beach paradise with a front door hand-carved from Bali. Bamboo floors & cabinets. Perfect for peaceful retreat or launch point for breathtaking sights & adventures.
neighborhood_overview:
This is in a dream location! At the edge of the neighborhood, you can hike the Redwoods via "The Enchanted Trail" or other hikes from De La Viega Park trailheads just a walk from your front door. 3 famous beaches are within 2.5 miles, and also UC Santa Cruz. You can drive 6 miles to renowned Henry Cowell State Park or 7 miles to the Forest of Nicene Marks State Park.

There's charm galore, w/ downtown Santa Cruz restaurants & shops along Pacific Ave an easy bike ride away (1.5 miles, and we have bikes for you), plus darling neighboring towns - Capitola, Aptos & Soquel.

Enjoy hot tub soaks under the stars or Backyard BBQ (by appointment, available most nights).

Though u feel like you're in a faraway beach paradise, you can also get to the heart of Silicon Valley (Apple, LinkedIn, Googl & Facebk HQs are 35-40 mins away--and employee shuttles pick-up right near) and San Jose airport is just a 33 min drive. Day trips to San Francisco are also easily access
host_about:
Hi, We're Christy and Barry...We are Adventurers who have been jazzed to be Airbnb Guests for over a decade. Our most priceless Airbnb memories are when we unplugged from our Silicon Valley life with our 2 kids and traveled around the world together for half a year, living and volunteering in Orphanages in rural villages in India, Thailand, Kenya, Uganda and Honduras. As we traveled between those countries, we stayed in Airbnb homes in between (Spain, Italy, Athens, Amsterdam, Iceland, and more).  We were warmly welcomed at every stay. 
We just became empty nesters with our kids away to college/Post-college, so we bought a home in one of our favorite places on earth -- Santa Cruz, where breathtaking Redwoods meet the shore in a charming beach community. We are so excited to live in Santa Cruz now and explore all its beautiful treasures, Learn the rich history, and enjoy this inclusive, thoughtful community.  

We were taken by this home when we saw the For Sale sign on an Anniversary sSanta Cruz visit. The owner Ted wanted to create a little tropical paradise and it was so clear that she had done so as an absolute labor of love. (You’ll see the hand carved doors from Bali and other authentic tropical touches). We moved into the home as soon as we could and we now spend alternate weekends caring for my aging mom in our former town, so when we are able, we love being able to provide magical, memorable Guest experiences for Guests, just as our Hosts have done for us around the world. <3

neighborhood_overview: Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.

name: Ocean View Bedroom at Rio Del Mar Beach
description: Get away & relax in a peaceful, gorgeous Mediterranean hillside home nestled in the hills of Rio Del Mar in Aptos (Hosted Rental Permit #241003).  A separate entrance is down the stairs, & through a gated backyard. Enjoy ocean, beach, & shore views directly from your patio & bathroom window. A private sauna/steam room is connected through a room equipped with a refrigerator, microwave, hot water kettle, coffee maker, utensils, etc. Enjoy an outdoor hot tub, fire pit, BBQ, & indoor theater room.
neighborhood_overview:
There are several excellent restaurants and Deluxe Foods supermarket, and Cvs pharmacy in Rio Del Mar, Aptos. I highly recommend the following:
1. Red Apple Cafe for breakfast or lunch
2. Bittersweet Bistro Cafe for lunch or dinner
3. Deluxe Foods for groceries & deli, and fresh meats and seafood, etc.

In the town of Capitola:
4. Shadowbrook restaurant for a very nice meal and celebration
5. Margaritaville restaurant for lunch or dinner
6. Paradise grill restaurant for lunch or dinner
7. Zelda’s restaurant on the beach for breakfast, lunch, or dinner
8. Caruso’s Italian restaurant for dinner

The Guidebook provides recommendations for nearby restaurants, supermarkets, beaches, hiking, fishing, shopping, and golfing.
host_about: I Love living near the ocean and I believe the best dreams really do come true.

host_about:
We've been helping people make terrific Santa Cruz Memories for generations.  Let us assist in making your next beach vacation amazing.

Kendall & Potter was established as a real estate company over fifty years ago. 
The brokers Skipper Kendall and William Potter moved to Aptos to fulfill their dream of working in a small town in Santa Cruz County. They soon expanded their services to include property management and relocation to Santa Cruz County along the Monterey Coast.

Kendall & Potter continues to be seen as one of the leading forces in Santa Cruz County Real Estate Property Management.

Rita Law, now owner and broker, purchased the property department and has been on site for nearly 50 years.

Kendall & Potter Property Management offers a variety of home services – including complete property management services, leases on unfurnished properties and rental homes in Santa Cruz, as well as Monterey Coast & Santa Cruz vacation rentals management and corporate housing.

name: Beach Bungalow in a central location
description: Come enjoy a peaceful beach bungalow that is centrally located in a quiet neighborhood.  We are moments away from some of the most desired beaches: 1.8 miles from New Brighton State Beach, 2.5 miles to Seacliff State Beach, and 1.9 miles to beautiful Capitola. We are 4 miles from Nisene Marks State Park which is great for hiking and mountain biking. We have kitchen that includes a sink, microwave, fridge, gas stovetop, and a Keurig coffee maker. The space also has a full sized pull-out couch.
neighborhood_overview: We are a 5 min drive to downtown Soquel, Aptos, and Capitola. Downtown Santa Cruz is a 10 min drive. Jump in the ocean and go for a surf we have surf boards and boogie boards available. We are moments away to some of the most desired beaches, 1.8 miles from New Brighton State Beach, 2.5 miles to Seacliff State Beach, and a 1.9  miles to beautiful Capitola Village.  Cabrillo College is 1 mile away with a wonderful farmers market open on Saturday’s.
host_about: My husband (Jeff) and I (Annie) are excited to share our space with you. We hope you enjoy beautiful Soquel/Aptos/Santa Cruz as much as we do.

name: Peaceful Corralitos Farm! + Free Aquarium Tickets
description: This cozy guest casita is perfectly located for exploring the Monterey Bay area like a local or relaxing, listening to songbirds by day and crickets by night. Our guest casita has its own entrance and all the amenities you'll need. The vibe is carefree, relaxed, calm and welcoming on our 20 acre farm, complete with chickens, fruit trees, cane berries, and lavender fields.
neighborhood_overview:
Corralitos is a gem in Santa Cruz County! The town is comprised primarily of apple orchards, vineyards, and beautiful views. We are a 5 minute drive from the famous Corralitos Meat Market and other restaurants/shops in town.

The east side of Santa Cruz is 15 minutes from the property, where you'll have your pick of beautiful beaches, redwood hiking, excellent restaurants and coffee shops.

The Monterey peninsula, 17 mile Drive, and Carmel by the Sea is less than an hour away, with Moss Landing restaurants, kayaking and beaches just 25 minutes away.

We love this area and want you to experience it like a local. All of our best tips and places to explore are included in our guidebook and we're more than happy to provide additional recommendations and tips!

Most of our houseguests don't want to leave ;-) Husband speaks German and some French.

name: Updated Westside home. 4 blocks from the beach!
description:
Kick back and relax in this calm, stylish space. Newly renovated 2 bedroom 1 bath home near Steamer Lane.

Awesome Westside location. The best part of town.
You can hear the waves crashing when they are big, and the sea lions barking at night.

Hardwood floors, new paint, new beds, new linens, new towels.
60" flat screen with Fire Stick.
Indonesian furniture.

4 blocks to the beach. 3 blocks to lighthouse park.
Easy access to Hwy 1 to drive up the coast.
host_about:
I travel often and I appreciate good hospitality. 
Before CoVid I used to spend about 1/2 the year operating the eco surf resort my friend and I built, in the Mentawai Islands of West Sumatra, Indonesia. 

While the world has been shut down 
I've renovated my house to rent on Air BnB. 
I lock my bedroom door, making it a 2 bedroom 1 bathroom house. 

It makes me happy to help other people make themselves happy! 
I Love Santa Cruz, especially the Westside. 
We have an awesome, quiet neighborhood, so close to the beach you can hear the waves crashing and the sea lions barking at night.

You will have the whole house to yourself. I do Not stay at the house while it is rented.

name: Oceanfront Retreat with epic sunsets steps to sand
description:
Epic views and steps away to feel the sand between your toes in a highly desirable gated Shorebirds Resort community. From our front door, you are greeted with amazing ocean views. You can hear the sound of waves from the bedroom or living room. Beautifully remodeled 2bed, 2bath sleeps 6 people easily.

The vibe is relaxation to miles of beautiful ocean and nature located between Monterey and Santa Cruz County. Personally, I enjoy watching all the birdlife as well in the lagoon and along the beach.

name: The Commodore’s Cottage, Stroll Twin Lakes Beach
description: Sunny two-bedroom beach cottage a few short blocks from Twin Lakes beach and the Santa Cruz yacht harbor. The large backyard with BBQ is perfect for entertaining. Short walk to the beach. Wonderful kids park with tennis and basketball court across the street and yes, tennis racquets and balls are included. We're located directly next door to one of Santa Cruz's best breakfast spots, the Harbor Cafe. And private off-street parking is available for up to two vehicles for those of you driving in!
neighborhood_overview: Twin Lakes has become a well-loved beach by locals and tourists, and Woods Lagoon now harbors hundreds of fishing and pleasure boats. The slightly warmer water (compared to Seabright) and sandy seafloor make for some great bodysurfing here, and the freshwater that flows onto the beach from Schwan Lake is a sandcastle architect’s dream. Towards the harbor end of the beach, athletic types can challenge each other to a game of beach volleyball, while the not-so-sporty among us can watch from one of several ocean view restaurants. If you’re on vacation (or not), go ahead and eat your way through the day here: start the morning with coffee or cocktails directly nextdoor at The Harbor Cafe, fuel up on Mexican fare at Cafe El Palomar for lunch, and after a long day in the sun, enjoy dinner and drinks at The Crow’s Nest on the upper deck overlooking the harbor channel.
host_about: I’m an evergreen optimist and a life long learner. When I’m not traveling the world with my wife and kids (or day dreaming about it), I enjoy catching live music, participating in a good jam session, reading, snowboarding,  and spending as much time as possible on a boat pulling up crab pots!

name: One block from the beach 1 BR 1BA Hawaiian hidaway
description:
This is a long-term vacation rental for 30 days or more. Perfect for snowbirds or people who want to live and work close to the beach. You don't have to go far to enjoy the sun and surf.
One block from the beach located off of East Cliff Dr. between Capitola and Yacht Harbor. This hideaway is ideal for a couple. It is a second-story one-bedroom, one -bath is warm, comfortable and very inviting. Gourmet kitchen and great room look out at an outside deck, which has a BBQ and a view of the lagoon.
host_about: We are the Talbot family. We bought our vacation home when our kids were 9 and 12. We wanted a place we could enjoy the beach, but also share that experience with others like you.  We wanted to embrace the Santa Cruz lifestyle with a beach house-style home.    I was born and raised in Hawaii, and I wanted a home away from home. So the island decor fits perfectly with the house location to the surf, beach, and the Aloha Grill down the street.  Our kids love the bunk beds, and we made one of the rooms into a surfer decor to bring the Santa Cruz surf style to life. The beach, which is a short walk away, was perfect for beach lovers alike.  It has boogie boarding, surfing, great sand for sandcastles, and wonderful views. The beach has no public parking, so it is inhabited by mostly locals and doesn't get too crowded. Also, at night it is a great beach for bonfires.  We hope you enjoy the house!

neighborhood_overview:
Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.

name: Relaxing Beach House: 1 min to Privates Beach
description: This charming beach house is the perfect getaway for anyone looking to relax and unwind by the ocean. Located just a short walk from Privates Beach and other popular surf spots, the house offers the perfect combination of convenience and seclusion. The cozy and inviting interior features original 1950s wood floors and crown molded ceilings, giving it a warm and nostalgic feel. And with plenty of shops and restaurants nearby, you'll have everything you need to enjoy the laid-back beach lifestyle.
neighborhood_overview:
Just a short walk away to the west, you'll find the Private's Beach Gate, providing public access to a fantastic local cove. The beach is perfect for a day of relaxation and you can take your pick at the fun right-hand point break to surf. The treetop cabin is a perfect place to unwind and retreat, and then to adventure into the incredible nature that surrounds you.
Now (2024) with superfast Wifi for work vacation.

The nearest town is Felton with a small but lively mountain community of great natural food stores, cafes, local boutique shopping, restaurants, music, wineries, and taverns. It is truly a gem! We’re happy to offer our local recommendations - just ask!

neighborhood_overview: Rio Del Mar Beach is the main beach in the community of Rio Del Mar in Aptos, CA. This long wide sandy beach is the southern part of Seacliff State Beach. These beaches on Monterey Bay are continuous so you can walk in either direction for miles.

neighborhood_overview:
Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.

This is not a good place for gatherings or parties so please keep that in mind when booking this home. We are very respectful of our neighbors and will not tolerate loud noise past curfew and additional guests at the property.

neighborhood_overview:
Located just south of Santa Cruz off Highway 1, Seascape Beach Resort gorgeous accommodations overlooking the Monterey Bay.
The entire resort sits atop breathtaking bluffs overlooking the ocean and beaches below. The walking path in the center of the resort leads down to the beach.
On the resort you will find The Seascape Park, Numerous walking paths, The Sanderlings Restaurant and bar, 3 pools and spas, and a full gym (gym access with additional fee paid on-site).
Across the street from the resort you will find Seascape Village which offers restaurants, cafes and shops.
The PGA rated Seascape Golf Course is only 5 minutes from the resort.
In the Heart of Aptos just over three miles or 10 minutes drive away you will discover what happens when the redwoods meet the sea. This idyllic setting is perfect for mountain biking, hiking or exploring the historic village. In the village you will meet the lovely people of Aptos who love their town and it's visitors. Pick

description:

neighborhood_overview:

We have nearby neighbors who can be heard from time to time talking or calling for their cats. While we have no control over our neighbor's noise, we ask that our guests be extremely mindful of volume, especially after 10pm.

Corralitos is a valley town in the south county of Santa Cruz. Just inland from the great Pacific, we tend to be 10 degrees warmer in the summer and rarely get the fog and wind of nearby La Selva. Excellent surfing, hiking and biking is all at your fingertips, just ask us for additional recommendations. Our quiet side street off Amesti is a great mix of cultures, ages and backgrounds. We're well aware it won't be long before this gem of a smalltown starts to change, so we're enjoying it while we can!
host_about: My wife and I live the valley of Corralitos. We love working on yard projects, finding time to be mellow, and enjoying the land we steward. We hope you enjoy your time in our most recent project, the Tanoak Casita, a little back house tucked in the trees.

name: Oceanview Family Playground
description: Family-friendly oceanview home at Pleasure Point. This inviting retreat offers a backyard play area, including a water table and climbing structure for the little ones. Enjoy outdoor dining, the BBQ grill, the hot tub, hammocks. Inside, take in two living areas, two en-suite bedrooms, toys, playhouse, and baby amenities. EV charger in garage. Nearby, find great surfing spots, a coastal bike trail, Capitola Village, and Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk. Create memories at your Pleasure Point home!
neighborhood_overview:
Pleasure Point in Santa Cruz is a captivating coastal destination that embodies the essence of California beach culture. Located along the scenic Monterey Bay, this vibrant neighborhood offers a unique blend of natural beauty and laid-back charm.

Pleasure Point is renowned for its world-class surf breaks, attracting surfers from all over the globe. Watch in awe as skilled riders carve through the waves, showcasing their talent and creating an exhilarating spectacle. The rhythmic crashing of the surf and the salty ocean breeze create a mesmerizing atmosphere that embodies the spirit of the ocean.

Beyond its renowned surf spots, Pleasure Point offers breathtaking coastal views and picturesque landscapes. Take a leisurely stroll along East Cliff Drive, where you can admire the stunning vistas of the Pacific Ocean and take in the sights and sounds of this coastal paradise. The coastal path is perfect for biking, jogging, or simply enjoying a peaceful sunset walk.
host_about: My wife, Wendy, and I came to the Monterey Bay Area to work as educators at local schools. I now dedicate my time helping others enjoy our area as much as we do and Wendy continues working with students with special needs. We love meeting new people, learning about cultures, and traveling. We have two little ones that light up our life and we want to show them the world.

name: Palisades Casita at Pleasure Point - 30 Day Rental
description: Stay at this cute beach cottage, steps away from world-class surfing and the ocean! This one-bedroom, one-bath unit also has a living area with a smart TV equipped for streaming and a kitchenette. It's comfortable, clean and a great place to call home while visiting Santa Cruz!  30+ day Min Stay.  Fully Furnished with Utilities Included.
neighborhood_overview:
Pleasure Point is a beloved coastal neighborhood. Known for its world-class surfing, laid-back ambiance, and breathtaking ocean views, it's a haven for beachgoers and water enthusiasts. The iconic surf breaks like "The Hook" attract surfers from around the world. This vibrant community boasts a unique blend of surf shops, cafes, and local boutiques. Stroll along East Cliff Drive, savor fresh seafood, or catch a mesmerizing sunset from the cliffs. With its bohemian spirit and proximity to the lively Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, Pleasure Point offers a quintessential California beach experience.

This is not a good place for gatherings or parties so please keep that in mind when booking this home. We are very respectful of our neighbors and will not tolerate loud noise past curfew and additional guests at the property.
host_about: O'Neal Vacation Rentals is a small team that is laser focused on hosting guests at amazing vacation rentals! We believe that memorable vacations are centered around beautiful homes that are comfortable and stocked with all the amenities that make for an amazing stay.

neighborhood_overview:
Located just south of Santa Cruz off Highway 1, Seascape Beach Resort gorgeous accommodations overlooking the Monterey Bay.
The entire resort sits atop breathtaking bluffs overlooking the ocean and beaches below. The walking path in the center of the resort leads down to the beach.
On the resort you will find The Seascape Park, Numerous walking paths, The Sanderlings Restaurant and bar, 3 pools and spas, and a full gym (gym access with additional fee paid on-site).
Across the street from the resort you will find Seascape Village which offers restaurants, cafes and shops.
The PGA rated Seascape Golf Course is only 5 minutes from the resort.
In the Heart of Aptos just over three miles or 10 minutes drive away you will discover what happens when the redwoods meet the sea. This idyllic setting is perfect for mountain biking, hiking or exploring the historic village. In the village you will meet the lovely people of Aptos who love their town and it's visitors. Pick

neighborhood_overview:
Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.

name: NEW! May’s log cabin luxury studio farm stay.
description: Relax & recharge at this rural homestead in Los Gatos. Whether you’re here to reconnect with nature, hike the trails, camp under the stars, or explore the Bay Area, May’s Log Cabin Studio offers private luxury accommodation in a rustic mountain setting. With nature trails on-site and the Saratoga Gap down the road you won’t have to go far conveniently located between Silicon Valley & Santa Cruz. The property offers sweeping views of the Pacific Ocean, mountains and the South Bay from 2800ft.
neighborhood_overview:
Our homestead is located at the end of a private road: Snow Crest Road. We are the last of four properties in a very rural setting. Your studio apartment is over 100 yards away and facing away from our nearest neighbors. This is a working property that we’ve saved from likely demolition. We are two years into its transformation. You may see us working in the upper acreage and tending to our animals, pond and small orchard. We won’t be make much noise but you’ll occasionally see us working on the land.

Guest parking is in front of the middle of three garage doors. Additional parking is provided in the large crushed granite driveway and parking area above.

Also please note that this is a rural setting. Noise travels. Please be aware that you may hear occasional road noise.
host_about: I’m from Thailand and live on our homestead in the Santa Cruz Mountains with my husband Jon and son Harlan. And of course our goose Tony.

name: 3868 Emerald House - Completely Remodeled Capitola
description: This unit is a monthly rental. We request that all nights of your stay are within the same month. Some exceptions may be made, with the approval of our team and the homeowner. Payment of a Security Deposit via credit card to Sanctuary Vacation Rentals will be required at time of booking.   Please refer to our House Rules for further information. 1,475 sf, 3 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom vacation home sleeps up to 6 guests. King, Queen, Queen. Bonus room. Dog OK. No garage.
host_about:
Sanctuary Vacation Rentals represents properties throughout Carmel, Pebble Beach, Pacific Grove, Carmel Highlands, and the Big Sur coastline. We combine fine resort accommodations and relaxed elegance with all the comforts of home. 
Our properties are places that nurture and inspire and are located in one of the most beautiful, energizing places in the world, featuring the spectacular scenery of the Monterey Peninsula and the central coast of California.  From historic old Monterey, to the Victorian charm of Pacific Grove, and the artists colony of Carmel-by-the-Sea, and the breathtaking scenery of Big Sur, generations of people have been rejuvenated by the breaking waves and sandy beaches here.
Our properties are designer furnished with relaxed elegance.  Many homes feature the colors of the sea and take inspiration from the natural beauty of the surrounding areas.
Throughout Sanctuary’s vacation rentals, you’ll find comfortable beds with luxury linens, welcome beverages and hors d’oeuvres, spa robes and amenities, local wine tasting and spa passes, and a personal concierge to assist you in every way.  Our homes feature chef’s dream kitchens and everything you’ll need to entertain in style.  And many of our properties are pet friendly.
If you’re looking for a refreshing, relaxed stay in one of the most beautiful areas in the world– offering all the comforts of home, let Sanctuary Vacation Rentals help you discover your own sanctuary by the sea.  

The Monterey Peninsula is unique in its combination of breathtaking natural resources and a multiplicity of cultural and entertainment possibilities. You can find something for every possible taste. For nature lovers, there is the diversity of mountain and sea, for picnicking, surfing, fishing, horseback riding, hiking, beach-combing, bird-watching, kayaking, scuba diving, tide-pooling, biking and more. If you want a man-made excitement, we have art galleries galore, excellent fine-art museums, local theatre, outstanding restaurants, boutiques, a natural history and a children's museum, a world-class aquarium, and that's just for starters. History buffs will have a field day exploring the adobes of Monterey. There's so much to do that you cannot possibly do it all in one visit, which means you will have to come back.

description:

neighborhood_overview: The Venetian courts, styled after the Mediterranean architecture of Venice, is charming, unique, and transports you into a different world. We think #5 has the best location as it is front and center, with the sand coming right up to the sea wall.

There is a community playground close to the cabin. There are rules around using this playground. If you do use it, please inform the host so we can be aware and take all precautions necessary. There is a zip line and this can only be used by children 60 pounds or less. The playground is a lot of fun but please adult supervision at all times.

Helping other owners with their properties here in town has been a delightful way of sharing the best parts of Santa Cruz and the Bay Area with people vacationing in our airbnbs. Here to help of you need anything!

neighborhood_overview:
The Santa Cruz Mountains surround our quaint small cabin on our large wooded property. This cabin is the perfect location to explore Santa Cruz beaches, mountains and culture or just to get away from it all and relax.

This quintessential California beach town is a mecca for surfers and sun-worshippers, but also has something for everyone. Families love visiting the famous Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, while nature lovers appreciate the area's many unspoiled beaches.

Santa Cruz is a popular place for summertime recreation, from volleyball to boating and hiking. The breathtaking scenery and refreshing sea breezes make this stretch of California's Central Coast especially appealing.

HIKING

name: Forest Cabin Retreat
description: Take it easy at this unique and tranquil getaway. Situated in the beautiful north coast mountains of Santa Cruz amongst the redwoods. Our south facing lot invites the Pacific Ocean breeze, and lush vegetation. Experience nature in comfort and style in our beautiful little cabin in the woods. Only 15 minutes to UCSC, 15 minutes to the charming town of Felton, 20 minutes to Santa Cruz, 10 minutes to the north coast beaches. Near world renowned biking trails, hiking trails, nature reserves, etc.
neighborhood_overview: Bonny Doon is a special place. It hosts a variety of micro climates and vistas. From the majestic redwood forest to chaparrals, to manzanita and madrone forests it is truly a magical place. We hope our guests take some time to explore the ecological reserve (3 minute drive from our place), the great and famous giant redwood, ‘Big Ben, just up the street from us, the hundreds of world class biking trails that can be accessed along the beautiful Empire Grade Road. The new state park, part of the Coast Diaries and so much more! Our property sits at about 2000 feet elevation, sometimes in the winter months we get a beautiful dusting of snow. It’s south facing and on clear days if you hike up the property there is a little window view of the Pacific Ocean. neighborhood_overview: Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.

host_about:
I am a retired nurse who specialized in labor and delivery, and post partum care. For over forty years I have taught childbirth classes and parenting classes in both English and Spanish. For a number of years when my daughter was young, I was a co-director of a co-op pre-school.  I founded and was director of a Family Resource Center for 10 years, and then took a great sabbatical that was full of traveling,  hiking the John Muir Trail, and climbing Mt. Whitney and Mt. Rainer. For a number of years I did hospice nursing, and now I have retired from nursing and I am spending a lot of time with my grandson and his parents in Florida.  
My dad was a rower at Cal in 1939, and my 100 year old aunt just rowed a 2000 meter in 19:27. The book The Boys in the Boat is a really fun read.

neighborhood_overview:
Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.

name: Zen mountain room with hot tub and a view
description:
Welcome to a peaceful room above the clouds!

Surround yourself in nature at this unique and tranquil getaway. Explore the great hikes around us, then come back to watch the sunset from above the clouds while you relax and unwind in the hot tub. neighborhood_overview:
Our property is located in a community of homes within Castle Rock State Park!

Paradise location for hikers, backpackers, cyclists, and nature explorers. You'll find trails that cut through our community and connect us to the park and to some famous trails around, like Saratoga Gap and Skyline to the Sea. Big Basin Redwoods State Park is also just a few minutes away.

Skyline Blvd offers endless trails, lookouts, and wineries to explore. The famous Alice Restaurant is just a short drive away.

If you need to access the city, the closest one is Saratoga, about 20min driving.

neighborhood_overview:
The Santa Cruz Mountains offer a serene escape from the hustle and bustle. This lush and forested region is a nature lover's dream, featuring towering redwood groves, hiking and biking trails, and pristine state parks like Big Basin Redwoods State Park. With picturesque vistas, it's an idyllic setting for outdoor activities, including birdwatching and camping. The Santa Cruz Mountains also boast a thriving wine scene, with vineyards and wineries producing exceptional varietals. It's a place to unwind, disconnect, and find solace in nature's beauty, making it a perfect retreat for those seeking tranquility and outdoor adventure.

neighborhood_overview:
Aptos is a coastal gem nestled in Santa Cruz County. With its stunning beaches, including Rio del Mar and Seacliff State Beach, it's a haven for sun-seekers and surf enthusiasts. This charming town boasts a laid-back vibe, a mix of boutique shops, and a vibrant dining scene, making it a perfect destination for a relaxing vacation. The iconic Cement Ship at Seacliff Beach is a must-see, and nearby forested parks like Nisene Marks offer hiking and biking trails. Aptos combines natural beauty, small-town charm, and easy access to the Santa Cruz Boardwalk, creating an ideal coastal escape for visitors.

This is a very quiet, family neighborhood. It is not a good place for gatherings or parties so please keep that in mind when booking this home. We are very respectful of our neighbors and will not tolerate loud noise past curfew and additional guests at the property.

description: Experience a unique coastal getaway nestled on its own private beach area in Pajaro Dunes, California. The house offers seclusion and tranquility, allowing you to immerse in the natural landscape. Relax on the patio or by the oceanfront firepit, embracing the beauty of the ocean at your doorstep. neighborhood_overview:
Pajaro Dunes is a beautiful beach community located on Monterey Bay in California. While Pajaro Dunes itself is a serene retreat known for its sandy beaches and natural beauty, there are plenty of attractions and activities to explore in the surrounding areas such as Watsonville, Santa Cruz, Moss Landing, Carmel, Monterey, and Big Sur. Here are some things to do in each of these nearby cities:

1. Watsonville:
- Visit the Watsonville Plaza for a taste of local culture and history.
- Explore the Agricultural History Project Center & Museum to learn about the region's farming heritage.
- Enjoy outdoor activities at nearby parks like Pinto Lake Park and Ramsay Park.

2. Santa Cruz:
- Spend a day at the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk for amusement park rides and entertainment.
- Visit the Santa Cruz Wharf for seafood dining and scenic views.
- Explore the Santa Cruz Surfing Museum and learn about the area's surfing history.

neighborhood_overview:
Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.
